title: richard's famous german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Smear 1/2 stick margarine (softened) over bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Spread all the pecans and coconut on the bottom.
Prepare the German chocolate cake mix according to instructions on the box and pour on top.
Now, here's the good part!
Add a mixture of 1 stick margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spoon evenly on top of the cake batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unwind dough and press out on a large cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 8 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crumble cookies, add melted butter and press into a 9-inch pie tin.
Beat cream cheese, egg, 8 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla together; pour in crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes in fridge.
Beat 12 ounces sour cream, 5 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla together; pour on cheese cake.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Chill 6 to 8 hours. Top with 4 ounces sour cream.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover with crushed crackers. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown beef.
Stir often to keep broken apart; drain off excess fat.
Add 1 quart of water, potatoes and salt to meat; cook until potatoes are tender but not done.
Add all remaining ingredients; simmer for about 20 minutes.
May need to add more water if it is not soupy enough.
Can add 1 cup of egg noodles if you like noodle soup.
Cook them with potatoes and meat.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixing bowl. Add sugar, salt and half of the flour (approximately 3 1/2 cups). Beat thoroughly. Add egg and shortening.
Beat in remaining flour. Cover with damp cloth. Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally.

title: fat-free angel food cake with lemon glaze
directions: Sift flour with half the sugar.
In a large whipping bowl put the whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla and whip until soft peaks form.
Then begin adding the rest of the sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, whipping well in between each addition.
Continue until stiff peaks form, then sift a quarter of the flour mixture over top.
Fold into whites with a spatula, gently.
Fold in remaining flour by quarters.
Carefully, pour into an ungreased angel tube pan and gently cut the batter through here and there with a knife to remove air pockets.
Bake 40 minutes or until lightly golden on top.
Cool cake upside down on top of a funnel for an hour, then run a knife around the edges and unmold onto a plate.

title: bud's favorite cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage.
While sausage is browning, cube cheese and pour in a large pot or crock-pot on low.
As cheese is melting, add all other ingredients.
After sausage is cooked, drain and add.
Serves an army.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together oats, wheat germ, bran, coconut, and nuts.
In a glass measuring cup, combine honey and oil.
Microwave until it boils (approximately 2 minutes).
Watch carefully.
Pour oil and honey over oat mixture, and stir to coat all.
Using 2 large cookie sheets or baking pans, divide oat mixture evenly, and spread as thin as possible.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Stir and spread. Bake 10 minutes.
Stir and spread.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, combine both halves, and add dried fruit.
Store airtight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Heat Ro-Tel and melt cheese in it. Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add to tomato and cheese mixture.
Add bell pepper, mushrooms and olives.
Add boned chicken which is cut in big pieces.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
If you wish, add more cheese on top before baking.

title: frozen apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1/2 cup of liquid.
Stir liquid into eggs.
Add sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook on top of stove, stirring until mixture thickens (about 5 minutes over medium heat).
Cool.
Fold drained pineapple, apples, celery and whipped cream into cooled dressing.
Spoon into 9-inch dish.
Cover and freeze.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain in cool water.
Add enough vinegar to mayonnaise to make it a salad dressing consistency.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Prepare a day ahead and add more mayonnaise, if needed, before serving.

title: souper chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the cheese and half of the onions.
Pour into casserole; bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and cheese; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: elegant tang pie
directions: Mix milk, sour cream, Tang, and lemon or lime juice together. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate over night.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on ham; cut pickle in 1/2 or green onion and lay on ham and cream cheese; roll up and cut into bite sizes.
Use toothpick to hold together.

title: potatoes anna
directions: Place in greased casserole dish and pour melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Layer mixture of cheese, chili sauce, crab meat and flaked parsley.

title: easy egg drop soup
directions: 1. Mix chicken broth with corn starch and bring to boil. Reduce heat to a simmer. Slowly add egg, stirring constantly, until egg forms lacy strands.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion as meat browns.
Drain fat and return beef-onion mixture to pan.
Add chili beans, tomatoes and chili powder.
Heat through and serve with grated cheese and crackers or corn chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crushed wafers and softened butter.
Work well.
Press into sides and bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: red cinnamon punch
directions: Heat 1 cup juice in small saucepan.
Add red candies, stirring over low heat until candy is dissolved.
Cool.
In a large pitcher or punch bowl, mix sugar and remaining juice with chilled red candies mixture.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: frosted cauliflower(microwave recipe)
directions: Clean cauliflower.
Place in covered casserole dish or wrap in plastic wrap.
Microwave on High power for 8 to 12 minutes, depending on size of head.
Let stand for 3 minutes.

title: carrot muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, honey, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
In another bowl, combine oil and 2 eggs.
Add to flour mixture; stir in carrot.
Spoon into 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Beat egg with water and place in shallow dish.
Dip eggplant slices into egg and then into pancake mix.
Fry in skillet in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper toweling.
Arrange eggplant slices in a square baking dish, covering with sauce and cheese.
Make a second layer of eggplant, sauce and cheese if needed.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: our family's favorite pasta salad
directions: Serves 10 to 12 as a side dish, serves 6 as a main dish.

title: apple harvest bake
directions: Grease 9 inch pie plate.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla; add apples and nuts.

title: bread salad
directions: Combine bread, tomatoes, onion, garlic, olives, Feta, grated cheese & basil in lg. mixing bowl.
Pour oil over all and mix well to combine.
Best if made ahead to allow flavors to blend.
Add black pepper and salt if needed.
Serves 8.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil over medium-low heat in a 3-quart saucepan. Add garlic.
Stir and cook until golden brown.
Add onion and cook until soft and golden, stirring frequently.
Add seasonings and tomato products.
Bring to a boil at medium-high, then reduce to low.
Cover loosely and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. The recipe yields 6 cups.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Place in shallow bake-and-serve dish.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and cheese.
Spread over the head of cauliflower.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve immediately.

title: niblets
directions: Mix cereals in a roaster.
Pour liquids over cereal mixture. Sprinkle on the spice mixture from a shaker.
Stir so that it is mixed evenly.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 225°.
Stir lightly every 15 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: In a double boiler, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add the 6 beaten eggs and milk.
Cook until thickened.
This will take 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add whipping cream, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in casserole serving dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown beef in skillet; discard fat.
Combine all ingredients except relish in cooker, stirring well.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, or on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in sweet relish.
Cook in crock-pot and spoon over hamburger buns or onion rolls.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti
directions: In larger skillet, brown ground beef with onion and salt. Drain grease. Stir in tomato paste. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to bubbling, then simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until ready to eat.

title: pecan patties
directions: Place
potatoes (quartered), onion, salt and water into blender and
chop
fine.
Mix
with remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Shape
into patties and bake on sprayed cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn over after 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and beat well after each.
Sift together flour, salt and soda. Add all together and add vanilla.
Crush potato chips and nuts. Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Take up hot.

title: eastern slaw
directions: In a small jar, combine the vinegar, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and salt.
Shake until salt dissolves.
Add the oil and shake again to combine. Shred the cabbage. A few hours before serving, combine cabbage, peas and dressing in a large bowl.
Toss to combine.
Can also add 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: I mix everything together and cook it, simmer, for an hour or until the carrots are cooked.

title: grammy grahams
directions: Spread icing on one cracker.
Spread peanut butter on the other.
Great snack when put together.

title: german meatballs "1940's"(serves 4)
directions: Combine beef, eggs, crumbs, 1/4 cup water, onions, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, bring remaining water to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes, brown sugar, raisins, lemon juice and ginger snaps.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Add meat balls to skillet; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: lemon filling for cake
directions: In a double boiler, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, water, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Stir until smooth.
Stir constantly while cooking until thick; boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add oleo. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Put between cake layers.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar and melt over low heat.
Let cool.
Add eggs and dry ingredients, then vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: individual strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix flour and shortening until completely mixed.
Add beaten eggs and milk slowly until it forms a soft dough.
Roll out until about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with large biscuit cutter. Bake in 475° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Split while still hot and butter.
Fill with sweetened and crushed strawberries. Put on top and cover with berries.
Top off with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Could use sliced peaches instead of strawberries.

title: potato-onion bake
directions: Slice potatoes and onions.
In greased casserole dish layer potatoes, onions and oleo.
Repeat until dish is full, ending with oleo on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are done. You may have to add more oleo during baking.

title: pecan pie iv
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Break eggs over mixture and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350°.
Put on bottom shelf of oven until it starts getting brown, then on top shelf for a few minutes.

title: stewed chicken breasts
directions: Cut off all excess fat and rinse chicken pieces under cold running water.
Place in large pot and cover with cold water.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Drain.
Save broth for soup or other chicken dishes.
Freeze remaining chicken pieces as desired.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.
This dip looks very good as it is so colorful.

title: best-ever salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips. Refrigerate up to 3 days.

title: tangy wiener pick-up
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine gravy mix and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave, uncovered, for 6 minutes. (Stir after 2 1/2 and after 4 1/2 minutes.) Serve with toothpicks.

title: chicken salad souffle
directions: Mix as a salad and place on bread crumbs, put 4 slices bread on top.
Mix together eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Add to onion and barely cover with hot water. Season with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Cook until soft.
Stir in can of cream of chicken soup.
Cut cheese into thin slices and stir in.
Stir until the cheese is melted.
Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 soup cans of milk, depending on how thick you prefer your soup.

title: pan-fried venison steaks
directions: Pound steaks thoroughly with sharp edged meat pounder.
Cut into serving pieces.
Dip steaks into cream and dredge in flour. Brown one side in hot butter.
Turn.
Salt and pepper to taste. Continue browning until second side is well browned.

title: pastry
directions: Stir flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add water and mix.
Roll on floured surface.

title: brownie delight
directions: Mix brownie mix (Martha White) or your choice.
Add the 2 extra eggs and more water to make consistency of cake batter. Cool completely after baking in 2 layers in 9-inch pans or Tiara pans.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar; beat with mixer. Add 1 carton Cool Whip and 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Combine sugar, cocoa and butter.
Bring to boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let cool.
While cooling, place one layer of brownies on plate.
Top with half of the Cool Whip mixture.
Place remaining brownie layer on top of this.

title: old fashioned egg salad
directions: Fix lettuce layers.
Pour dressing over the layers and mix well.

title: farmers' seafood boil
directions: Bring a gallon of
water with the crab boil and salt to a boil.
Add corn
and
boil
for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and boil for 10 minutes.
Add
onions
and
sausage and boil for 5 minutes. Add shrimp.
After
minutes, drain and serve with crusty bread and a cold beverage.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried homemade corn
directions: Shuck ears of corn.
Cut middle ways of corn, taking off top kernels only.
Then go back down the corn, getting the cream and juice.
Add your other ingredients:
flour, sugar, salt, pepper and water.
Let simmer over medium to low heat.

title: toll house double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan combine butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate morsels and vanilla extract.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to larger bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread into greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, soup mix and spinach together.
Use plain yogurt if you are dieting instead of mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine the juice of the pineapple with the sour cream and mix well.
Then add the lime Jell-O and pistachio pudding to the mixture.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple and mix well.
Last, add the marshmallows and mix all ingredients together.

title: thin maple pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine syrup, egg and milk; gradually add to other ingredients.
Beat until smooth, then add shortening.
Cook in frying pan on medium heat.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, powdered sugar and butter to form a dough.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat together eggs, lemon juice, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Pour over the baked crust.
Return to oven for 20 more minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Cover cracked wheat with cold water.
Let stand 30 minutes; drain.
Press out as much water as possible.
Place cracked wheat, parsley, tomatoes, onions and mint in a glass/plastic bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cracked wheat mixture and toss. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Garnish with ripe olives if desired.
Serves 6 (175 calories per serving).

title: crushed fruit tapioca pudding(yields 6 servings)
directions: Boil the water in the top of a double boiler over direct heat. Mix the tapioca and sugar and gradually stir into the boiling water.

When the ingredients are boiling, place them over rapidly boiling water and cook for five minutes, stirring all the time. Remove from the fire and after cooling slightly, fold in the crushed pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill the tapioca before serving.
Other crushed canned fruits, such as apricots or berries may be used in place of the crushed pineapple.

title: blueberry lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium bowl, stir flour, 1/2 cup sugar and the baking powder and salt.
Add blueberries and toss to coat.
In medium bowl, whisk milk, butter, egg and lemon peel.
Stir into dry ingredients until just combined.
Spread in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Prep time: 15 minutes.
Baking time:
20 minutes.

title: party meat balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, eggs, salt and pepper. Shape mixture into small balls.
Spray a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray to prevent sticking.
Place small meat balls into pan.

title: gerry's potatoes
directions: Boil and drain potatoes; add cheese and sour cream which are at room temperature; beat into potatoes while hot until fluffy.
Add salts and put in a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle paprika over.
Refrigerate overnight before baking.
Can be frozen for later use.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
(If frozen, bake 1 1/2 hours.)

title: georgia roast quail
directions: Place slice of bacon around each bird.
Add butter and bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes longer.
Baste with the drippings.
Serve with mashed potatoes and brown gravy.
Serves 6.

title: onion blossoms
directions: Peel onion, leaving root intact.
Cut vertically in quarters to within 1/2-inch of root.
Cut each quarter in thirds.
Place onion in boiling water 1 minute, then place in ice water for 5 minutes.
Loosen petals. Drain, cut side down.
Place flour in zip-top bag.
Add onion and shake to coat.
Dip onion in egg. Place cracker crumbs in bag.
Add onion.
Toss to coat.
Chill 1 hour.
Pour oil to depth of 3-inches in electric fryer or saucepan. Heat to 375°.
Fry onion 5 to 7 minutes or until brown. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt. Serve with honey mustard or Ranch-style dressing.
Makes 2 appetizer servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add egg yolks. Sift flour and soda. Add to mixture with buttermilk. Fold in nuts and coconut. Fold in egg whites. Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Form into balls and press with a fork. Bake at 325°
for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Drop cabbage leaves in boiling, salted water for a few minutes, until they are pliable.
Drain and dry cabbage.
Divide meat mixture into 12 parts.
Place 1 part on each cabbage leaf.
Roll leaves, tucking ends securely.
Place rolls, seam side down, close together in baking dish.

title: caramels
directions: Melt the oleo.
Add the brown sugar; stir until mixed well. Add the Karo and Eagle Brand; boil to 236°, stirring constantly. Add the vanilla and nuts, if desired; mix well.
Pour into buttered pans; chill 2 hours.
Cut, put in wrappers and store.

title: darn good pie
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended.
Set aside. Cream oleo and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well. Stir in eggs.
(This amount will fill 2 crusts.) Bake in unbaked crust (shallow pan) at 350° until it won't shake in the middle, approximately 50 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil with electric mixer.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating each one for 1 minute. Mix dry ingredients together and dates.
Add to mixture.
Fold in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump all ingredients in layer in order given into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not mix anything.
Bake 55 minutes; cool before cutting.

title: hot mushrooms on toast
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet.
Stir in the lemon juice, parsley and pepper.
Add mushrooms; heat through.
Melt 2 or 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Cut bread into 1 inch squares; fry until crisp.
Use a toothpick to secure hot mushrooms to each toast square.
Serves 6.

title: miracle quiche
directions: Drain cooked vegetables and place in a 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend 15 seconds and pour into pie plate.

title: peanut butter pom poms
directions: Melt butter; add peanut butter. Mix well. Pour over Rice Krispies and 10x sugar. Roll into balls.

title: baked red beets
directions: Scrub fresh beets thoroughly.
Place in oven and bake until tender.
Be careful not to prick them too much with a fork as this allows the flavorful juices to escape.
When done, peel and serve hot with bits of butter on top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash and onion; add sour cream, soup, carrots and water chestnuts.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix. Pour squash mixture into baking dish.
Top with margarine and dressing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coca-cola chili
directions: Spray 3-quart Dutch oven or pan with nonstick cooking spray. Cook beef, onion and celery over medium-high heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain excess fat.

title: clark bars
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water in heavy saucepan until candy thermometer registers 300° (do not stir while boiling).
While mixture is cooking, spread peanut butter in Teflon skillet (buttered), over bottom of pan.
Grease counter top or large baking sheet with butter.
When candy mixture reaches 300°, take off at once and pour into peanut butter; stir fast.
When it gets to bread dough like consistency, pat out on counter top with spoon and cut into pieces at once (easier to cut with scissors, takes 2 people).
After it cools, dip in melted chocolate.
(Melt chocolate on medium heat in top of double boiler.
If chocolate gets too thick, add a few drops of cooking oil.)

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in greased large Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and pour over rolls.
Layer, one at a time, the chopped nuts and pudding mix.
Slice margarine and place around rolls.
Cover pan with cloth or foil.
Let set on countertop overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Invert pan over large serving dish.
Let set a minute so syrup will cover rolls.
Serve hot.
(Can reheat in microwave.)

title: baked chow mein noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: dutch "pocket books"
directions: Divide pastry into 2 portions.
Roll 9 inches each.
Put half of the meat and vegetables for each half of dough.
Fold pastry over filling to form a pocket book and seal edges with fork.
Slit top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: zucchini-cheese appetizer squares
directions: Combine oil, onion and garlic; cook, stirring until almost limp, about 4 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook until tender-crisp. Mix eggs with bread crumbs, salt, basil, oregano, pepper, Cheddar cheese and zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and sesame seed.
Bake in 325° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until set when lightly touched in center.
Cut in 1-inch squares. Serve warm, room temperature or cold.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, milk and salt and mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Remove from heat; add vanilla and then half and half. Cool and pour into ice cream freezer. Freeze as directed.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Grease casserole slightly.
Butter one side of 4 slices of bread and place buttered side down in casserole.
Spread layer of ham, then second layer of bread (no butter), then layer of grated cheese.
Beat eggs in with milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Sprinkle coconut and 1/2 cup nuts over cake batter (optional).
Bake in cake pan with high edges.
Prepare pudding per instructions on box. Refrigerate.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In
a medium size bowl, combine salad oil, sugar, sesame oil, hot chili oil, soy sauce, rice vinegar and hot pepper.
Set aside.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Heat well.
Cut onions and peppers in small pieces and boil 10 minutes.
Drain and add to tomatoes.
Add vinegar, salt and garlic powder; heat well.
Put in jars and seal.

title: quick and easy turkey
directions: Wash turkey thoroughly.
Place in a roasting pan.
Melt butter. Add salt to butter.
Spread butter over turkey.
Chop celery and onion.
Stuff chopped vegetables inside turkey.
Place lid on roasting pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not open oven.
After 1 hour, turn off oven and leave turkey in oven overnight.
In morning or when ready to serve, uncover turkey and brown, using broiler section of oven.
Slice and serve.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Frost and store in refrigerator.

title: almond peach pie
directions: Slice peaches in pie shell.
Mix other ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
You may freeze these pies before baking.
Take out as you need and bake.

title: world's best chocolate cake
directions: Coat chocolate chips and pecans in 3 tablespoons dry cake mix. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: ham and cheese pop-ups
directions: Take one biscuit.
Flatten a little.
Place half slice of ham folded and half slice of cheese folded on top of flattened biscuit.
Flatten a second biscuit to cover ham and cheese.
Seal the edges of the two biscuits.
This makes one ham and cheese pop-up.

title: surprise cakes
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to package.
Fill cupcake holders (foil) 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese and combine with sugar.
Beat egg and salt until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoon cream cheese, sugar, egg, salt, chocolate chips in middle of each cupcake.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Dust with confectioners sugar.
Keep in refrigerator in covered container if not serving that day.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix together sugar, flour and egg.
Cook until thickened.
Put pineapple chunks in baking dish; add cheese to cooked mixture.
Put marshmallows over top of pineapple. Pour cheese mixture over top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples.
Turn into baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Dot with butter.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together	brown
sugar, shortening and oleo.
Add eggs and beat
well.
Then add flour, alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla,
salt
and
chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: easy nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 4 x 10-inch pan. Let stand 20 minutes to rise.
Bake in a moderate 325° to 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: glaze
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Thicken with cornstarch. Remove from heat.
Put in Jell-O.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Skin, remove excess fat, debone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Put bones, 1 stalk celery, 1 carrot and 1 onion in stockpot with 1 quart water; simmer for at least 2 hours for stock. Strain and set aside.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Dust chicken with flour and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of oil and add onions, bell pepper and celery. Saute until vegetables are wilted.
Return chicken to pot; add stock and garlic.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, adding stock if necessary.
Season with salt and pepper and add green onions and parsley.
Cook for 5 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, place pasta and cut up fresh vegetables.
Pour in 1/2 bottle of Italian dressing.
Put in olives and sprinkle with cheese.
Let chill for 2 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Finely crush graham crackers; melt butter.
Mix together and press into pan and bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: trisha's dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix with all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: egg rolls
directions: In a wok, fry hamburger with garlic and ginger; drain.
Add salt, pepper and sugar; mix well.
Add cabbage and cook with lid on for 3 minutes; add bean sprouts and bamboo shoots.
Cook for another 3 minutes.
Meanwhile in a cup, mix water, soy sauce and cornstarch; mix well and add to egg roll mixture.
Cook with lid off and allow mixture to thicken.
Set aside and let cool to room temperature.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg.
Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Beat applesauce into batter. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool.
Peel and grate into a large bowl.
Mix everything, except 2 tablespoons of butter which goes on top after you pat mixture into a buttered baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: applesauce pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil well.
Add orange juice and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add apples, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spring salad
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in a double boiler.
Mix cream cheese and dry lemon Jell-O.
Combine nuts, pineapple and mayonnaise; add to the marshmallow mixture.
Cool, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: creamy crab soup
directions: Pure soups and crab in food processor or blender. Mix all ingredients together and heat until hot, not boiling. That's it! If you don't have an ingredient, don't worry; this soup works well with substitutions. Holds well in crockpot set on low.

title: cheese herb sauce with noodles
directions: Saute
margarine,
green
onion and garlic cloves, then add flour and milk.
When thickened, add rest of ingredients. Serve over your favorite cooked noodles.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Heat 1 gallon water to boiling.
Pour out about 1 pint of hot water over 4 tea bags in a small pitcher.
Set aside to steep. Add rest of ingredients to remaining water. Simmer about 15 minutes. Add tea.
Simmer about 30 minutes longer.
Strain before serving. It will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: shrimp (baked, stuffed)
directions: Mix last 8 ingredients and stuff shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes (no longer).
Serve with melted butter.

title: french green split pea soup
directions: Remove ham and bone from ham liquid.
Skim fat from ham liquid when
cold.
Heat	liquid (approximately 3 1/2 quarts) and
add green split peas.
Bring to a boil, then simmer.
Add the vegetables	and simmer approximately 3 hours.
Remove ham from bone;
cube
and add to soup.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts. Consistency should be thick like stew.

title: raised dough
directions: Cream the butter with the flour.
Add sugar to egg yolks. Beat egg whites and add to yolks. Add sour cream or beer to egg mixture. Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dissolved yeast and add to flour.
Knead well.
Let rise overnight. Roll out and shape into nut rolls.
Let rise again in pans.
Bake in a 325° oven until brown.

title: creamy green bean bake
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk, 2/3 of the cheeses and 2/3 of the onion rings with the pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mixing well.
Sprinkel remaining cheese over mixture.
Top with remaining onions and bake in microwave, covered, 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat the oil and add the sliced onion.
Once the onion is brown, add the chicken, salt, cayenne, black pepper, garlic and ginger paste.
Cook over low heat to prevent the chicken from becoming tough.

title: "funeral beans"
directions: In large skillet, brown meat until red color disappears.
Drain off excess fat.
In slow-cooking pot (or range top in large pot on low heat), combine beef, dry dip mix, undrained pork and beans, drained remaining beans, catsup, mustard, chili powder, vinegar and brown sugar.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours (on stove top 1 1/2 hours).

title: nola's dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk; cream powdered sugar and cream cheese together and add to pudding.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip to that.
Put Cool Whip lid in the bottom of a plastic flower pot that has the bottom the same size of the Cool Whip lid.
Put 1/3 of the creamed mixture in the bottom of the flower pot.
Then add a layer of crushed Oreos.
Repeat 3 times, ending with crushed Oreos.
Use a new shovel as a serving spoon.
Place a bunch of plastic flowers in the pot.
Yum Yum Good!

title: fruitcake pudding
directions: Mix together.
Pour into well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40
minutes.
Sprinkle
brown
sugar
and nuts on top before baking, if desired.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice and onions in butter.
Pour in casserole dish and pour soup over (do not stir).
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles per package directions and drain.
Brown sausage, pepper, and onions in a Dutch oven or large saucepan, drain off grease.
Mix in all other ingredients and noodles.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until heated through.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix together, adding cherries last.
Put pieces of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Double this recipe for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: corn flake crunchies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in pan.
Cover; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes; stir until all are coated with syrup mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice to measure 1 cup.
Add to gelatin, stirring until ice is melted.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thick, and will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated beans
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, oil and seasonings.
Pour over vegetable mixture and refrigerate.

title: angels' delight
directions: Cut marshmallows into small pieces.
Add hot water, jello, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add crushed pineapple, cottage cheese and pecans.
Let stand until pretty firm.
Stir in whipping cream.
Set in refrigerator.

title: play clay
directions: Mix together. Work dough until smooth and holds together. Store in plastic bag or covered jar.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs, salt, vinegar and vanilla. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Raise temperature to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix 1/2 can of crushed pineapple (reserve remaining pineapple) with other ingredients and congeal.

title: mexican dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add meat.
Cut up flour tortillas.
Drop in broth. Bring to a boil.

title: asparagus-tomato stir-fry
directions: Snap off and discard woody bases from fresh asparagus.
If desired, scrape off scales.
Bias-slice into 1-inch pieces. Combine broth, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Set aside.
Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat; add oil.
Stir-fry ginger root in hot oil for 30 seconds.
Add asparagus and green onion; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Push from center; stir sauce.
Add to center of wok.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add tomatoes; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: hearty hamburger soup(yields 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Crumble beef in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave on Full Power for 3 to 5 minutes or until beef is no longer pink. Stir halfway through cooking time; drain.
Combine raw vegetables and 1/4 cup water in 4-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full Power for 11 to 13 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Mix in remaining ingredients and beef.
Cook, covered, on High for 30 to 35 minutes or until temperature of 150° is reached.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
May be adjusted for crock-pot.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix in a large pot the first 7 ingredients; simmer mixture while you saute the onion in olive oil in skillet.
When onion is golden, add hamburger and salt.
Cook until meat has lost its red color and add to the mixture in the pot.
Simmer for about 2 hours or until sauce is thick.

title: polish sausage and cabbage
directions: Place sliced cabbage in crock-pot.
Toss with diced potato, salt and caraway seed.
Add sliced onion and Polish sausage. Pour chicken broth over all; stir lightly.
Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 10 hours (high setting for 2 to 4 hours).
Serve with boiled new potatoes.
Makes 4 servings, 3 1/2 quarts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, zucchini, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add raisins, nuts and pineapple. Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, water and sugar until thick, the stir in dry jello and red coloring.
Pour over fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.

title: quick and easy pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with mixer.
Spoon into a graham cracker pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and
store
in
tightly
closed container. Add a few teaspoons to taste to 8 oz. hot water.

title: aaron's goose or duck combo
directions: Start water boiling.
Make roux with the flour and oil.
When roux is browned, add to boiling water.
Stir, adding onions, celery, bell peppers and the ducks or goose.
They can be chopped or whole.
Add rest of ingredients to taste.
Cover and simmer for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mounds
directions: Melt paraffin wax and chocolate bits together in a double boiler.

title: pepper steak
directions: Prepare ahead:
Cut steak in thin strips and marinate in the wine, soy sauce, sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in hot skillet (30 seconds).
Stir-fry peppers for 3 minutes; scoop out.
Heat 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add ginger and stir-fry for 2 minutes, then remove.
Stir-fry meat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add peppers and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring.
Serve over rice.

title: maryland crabbies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix garlic, Old Bay seasoning, mayonnaise, parsley and cheese; fold into crab meat.
Split English muffins; will have 12.
Spread mixture on English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: brass cleaner
directions: Mix equal amounts of each.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; pour into baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: roasted cauliflower
directions: Make cauliflower into 1-1/2 inch florets.
Cut red onions into 8 wedges.
Heat oven to 475°.
In non-stick roasting pan, mix cauliflower, onions, oil, salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Roast 15 minutes. Toss and roast 5 to 10 minutes until lightly charcoal and tender. Transfer to platter, top with 1/4 tsp. pepper, parsley and cheese.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest of liquids to make sauce.
Put meat mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Use tortilla shells for next layer.
Alternate to the top of the dish with meat and tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Put in 350° to 400° oven for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: dream jello
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups of hot water and 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Beat in a bowl until foamy.
Add cake filling.
Beat slightly more.
Fold in Cool Whip, leaving a little to ice with.
Refrigerate and use leftover Cool Whip to ice jello.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Place bacon strips on top. Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: pork and rice casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with remaining ingredients. Turn into a 6-cup casserole, cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot with tomato sauce if desired. Makes 5 servings.

title: rosemary's potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in large pot and add cold water to cover.
Heat to boiling, then lower heat and simmer, uncovered, just until fork-tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain in colander and let cool slightly.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a large bowl. Add cooked potatoes and mix gently to coat well.

title: coconut impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: yokome
directions: Mix together
ground beef, onions and pepper in skillet until done.
Cook
noodles
until tender in 2 cans tomato soup and 2 1/2
cans
water.
When ground beef mixture is browned, add to noodle mixture.
Continue cooking slowly for 1 hour.

title: pork and rice
directions: Boil meat until tender.
Remove meat from bones and set aside. Add more water to broth from meat to cook rice.
Cook rice according to package directions for approximately 15 minutes.
To one bag of rice, add 1/2 of meat and pepper to taste.
Then add other bag of rice and rest of meat and mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
This recipe heats well in the microwave.

title: potato dish or kartoffel fuusel
directions: Peel potatoes, then cover them with water.
Chop the onions small and fry them in oil.
Turn off heat and mix with salt and paprika.
Shred potatoes, then rinse in colander twice with cold water.
Squeeze out water and place in pot.
Mix well with fried onions.
Put in oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until soft and not stringy.
Remove from oven and stir them again.
Best served the next day.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: ronco mezzi rigatoni
directions: You can add hot peppers if you like them.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix together and let set for 20 minutes.
Stir.

title: bit of brittle ice cream dessert
directions: Trim angel food cake and cube.
Fold cake and Cool Whip; spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan.
Layer ice cream on top of cake.
Sprinkle bit of brittle.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: coconut-orange salad
directions: Arrange a circle of thick overlapping orange slices on crisp lettuce.
Heap coconut in center.

title: nachos(child snack recipe)
directions: Place chips on baking sheet.
Cover with ground beef; sprinkle with cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with salsa.

title: sausage splatters
directions: Fry sausage and drain grease.
Mix Bisquick, buttermilk, cheese, onion, bell pepper, sage, salt and pepper in with sausage. Spoon onto baking pan and bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: bohemian prune cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with liquids.
Mix in nuts and prunes.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 275° in three loaf pans.

title: donuts and cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together oil, yeast, sugar and water.
Let rise at least 10 minutes. Mix eggs and salt together.
Add to yeast mix with flour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix ingredients, mixing egg and oil last.

title: apple walnut bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brush with margarine and cut into cubes. Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes or until toasted.
Place in 8-inch square pan.
Add apples and walnuts.
Toss to mix.
Beat milk, egg product and vanilla in medium bowl with a whisk until well blended.
Add pudding mix and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes or until mixture comes to boil.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine onion and butter mixture with remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and freeze, uncovered, for 1 to 2 hours. When frozen place in a plastic bag and seal with a twistie tie. Keep frozen until ready to thaw for baking.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon of horseradish.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: To sour milk, add 2 tablespoons vinegar to 1 pint sweet milk.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together.
Boil hard for 6 minutes. Pour over Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter that have been combined in a large bowl.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
No need to heat.
Pour out on cookie sheet or into two 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix well. Let stand out of refrigerator all day (8 to 10 hours). This does not rise, only bubbles. Take out 1 cup to use in making bread. Return starter to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days, then feed again.
If not making bread after feeding, throw away 1 cup or give to a friend. Starter must be fed every 3 to 5 days.

title: veg soup
directions: Chop vegetables and place in large pot.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer.

title: busy day soup
directions: Break ground beef into small pieces.
Pour boiling water over meat and stir well.
Let stand 5 minutes and skim top.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: hot mulled punch(holiday crowd pleaser)
directions: Pour juices into a 24 to 30-cup coffeemaker.
Place remaining ingredients in coffee basket.
Let perk until cycle is completed. Remove basket.
Serve hot in mugs.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Bake.
As soon as brownies come out of oven, spread Marshmallow Fluff on top.
Cool.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover; chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: no potato-potato salad
directions: Make dressing by combining the beaten eggs, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until it bubbles and becomes thick.
Let cool.
Combine all other ingredients in a bowl.
Add the cooled dressing.
Mix well and serve.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Make up Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and whip until smooth. Add fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Stir in.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish so that pieces do not overlap.
Cover with mushrooms (no	juice).
Combine
mushroom soup, sherry and sour cream.
Stir	until
well
blended. Pour over chicken, completely covering it.
Dust
with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and add 4 cups fresh water. Bring to boil.
Simmer over medium heat for 1 hour or until done. Add all other ingredients and seasoning pack to taste.
Add more water if needed.
Cook 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: cole slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in airtight container until full. Have onions on top.
Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and pepper in pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oil. Let cool some and pour over cabbage and onion mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Make ahead.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick, about 5 or 10 minutes.
Stir all the time. Add 1 small box of strawberry jello to mixture and cool to room temperature.
In the meantime, bake 2 pie crusts and let cool. Put a pint of strawberries in each crust and pour the gelatin mixture over.
Let set several hours.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant in 1/4-inch slices. Salt and pepper. Shake in bag with flour and shake off excess. Fry in olive oil until golden brown. Saute onion, pepper, garlic, tomato sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste and parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste (not too much salt as cheese is salty). Cook sauce about 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bottom of two 8-inch loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture. Add bananas.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables and put in a bowl.
Mix dressing (other ingredients) and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush enough strawberries for 1 cup.
Combine crushed berries, honey, cornstarch and water in saucepan.
Stir to boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and let mixture cool. Place remaining whole berries in pie shell, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour cooked mixture over berries; chill 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Saute onion and green pepper slightly.
Add butter and flour. Boil giblets and use the broth to
thicken.
Chop up giblet and add cut up boiled egg.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix together and simmer about 3 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Add melted butter. Add peanut butter.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls. Let chill.
Using a double boiler, melt wax.
Add chocolate chips. Dip balls into chocolate mixture using a toothpick.
Coat each ball.
Place on wax paper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and syrup with hand beater.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake until set, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: coke cake
directions: Put sugar, flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Melt oleo over low heat, then add cocoa and Coke.
Heat to the boiling point and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Blend in marshmallows, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and soda.
Beat well.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: super punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well or until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale last.
Serve with ice ring made of cherries, orange slices and ginger ale, which has been frozen for several hours or overnight.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: In a large bowl, blend black-eyed peas and minced onion.
Add salsa, mayonnaise and avocado.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut dates into small pieces; add nuts and boiling water.
Allow to cool to room temperature (about 45 minutes).
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
On high speed with hand mixer, beat margarine with brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add dates; mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Place in 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until tester inserted in center of bread comes out clean.

title: bourbon slush punch
directions: Freeze 2 days and serve with 7-Up.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Cook together hamburger, bacon and chopped onion; drain.
Add the other ingredients and simmer or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carolina delights
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Drop immediately onto waxed paper and allow to set.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix flours together.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; mix well.
Heat milk, water and margarine together to 120° to 130°.
Pour in yeast mixture and beat for two minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour and beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Add enough remaining flour to make stiff batter.
Cover bowl tightly with foil or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Roll dough on floured board.
Cut rolls and place on buttered pans. Brush butter on tops of rolls.
Cover and let rise for about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: candied dills
directions: Drain dills, discarding juice, and cut each into 1/4-inch slices and repack in jar.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Cool slightly.
Strain out spices. Pour warm syrup over pickles.
Store in refrigerator for 1 week before using.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in 8-inch pan in order listed above.
Stir.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fancy fast chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top each piece of chicken with slices of Swiss cheese.
If using mushrooms, lay them over the cheese.
Mix the soup with wine and pour over chicken.
Spread stuffing mix over top and drizzle butter over stuffing mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: crab cocktail
directions: On a salad plate, place a nest of shredded lettuce; top with diced celery, then crab meat.
Leave space in the center for the cocktail sauce.
Either serve the sauce in miniature au gratin dishes or put directly on the lettuce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder soda and spices.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture and blend together.
Add shredded zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until it tests done.
Makes 1 large or 2 medium loaves.

title: canned stuffed banana peppers
directions: Put clove of garlic in bottom of each jar. Then cover with small layer of kraut. Clean banana peppers. Stuff with little kraut or either whole Li'l Smokies or pieces of hot dogs. Then pack in jars. In each jar, add 3/4 teaspoon sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons pickling salt and 1 teaspoon alum. For 8 quarts of pickles, put 2 quarts white vinegar and 2 quarts water in a pan. Bring to a boil. Pour into jars. Seal with lids. Process 10 to 15 minutes in hot water bath. You could use pint jars. Just use half of each thing the recipe calls for. Makes nice gifts.

title: no sugar banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas, Sweet 'N Low, flour and baking soda together. Add eggs.
Place in medium loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream wafers(makes 3 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar well.
Add egg.
Mix flour and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Then add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Place 1/2 pecan on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Line baking dish with pastry.
Save 1/2 of pastry for pie crust.
Fill crust with sliced green tomatoes.

title: refrigerated cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, sauerkraut, corned beef, onion, ketchup, mustard and Swiss cheese. Transfer dip to medium sized ovenproof casserole, covered. Bake 30 minutes or until bubbles form around the edges. Remove cover and bake 5 more minutes or until it turns golden. Serve warm with crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in a 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes (until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned).
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread on lightly buttered cookie sheet; cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first two ingredients. Cook, drain and mash. Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2-cup cheese to sprinkle over top. Pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 375° until firm and cheese is brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water per mix directions.
Set aside overnight in refrigerator.
Shred the lettuce, cut up tomatoes, onions and pepper.
Crush up the taco chips.
Add cheese and toss with dressing.

title: meatball subs
directions: Mix together the eggs, milk, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and the ground beef.
Form the ingredients into balls and cook on medium heat until done.

title: lemon broccoli(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broccoli, in a saucepan until margarine melts.
Pour over hot cooked broccoli.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Form into small balls.
Fry in hot Wesson oil turning frequently, until light brown but not crusty.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Mix well. Cover and simmer 4-5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix the flour and sugar.
Add milk, eggs, margarine (melted) and vanilla.
Mix on low speed.
Bake in a glass dish or pie plate for about 45 minutes at 300°.
No crust.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream all ingredients together until fluffy.
Will frost 1 (8 x 4-inch) cake.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed 2 minutes or until soft and creamy. Add sugar and beat at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Sift flour with the next 5 ingredients.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion juice.
Add oil slowly, beating with electric mixer.
Very good served over grapefruit, orange and avocado slices.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Spread on Waverly crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, cocoa, flour and vanilla.
Add milk.
Mix thoroughly and cook in heavy saucepan.
While cooking, add butter.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour into two prepared pie shells.
Top with egg white icing and brown.
Makes two pies.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in an 8 1/2 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted oleo. Cover top of casserole with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 9-inch pan; set aside.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Place sugar, cream of tartar, salt, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is completely dissolved, forming a syrup.
Place egg whites in bowl.
Beat on high until whites begin to hold shape, about 45 seconds.
Continue beating on high, slowly pour hot syrup into egg whites in a fine stream.
Add vanilla and continue whipping about 5 minutes, or until frosting loses gloss and stands in stiff peaks.
Frost cake immediately.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: goulash
directions: Mix oleo, onion and macaroni and cook a few minutes and stir while cooking.
In a skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato paste and water.
Mix all and cook slow until macaroni is done.
Top with slices of cheese.
Put lid on to let it melt; serve hot.

title: soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 4 hours in crock-pot or 1 1/2 hours on top of stove.
Serve with corn bread.

title: irish stew
directions: Cook meat until almost done.
Add potatoes, carrots, garlic salt, pepper and salt to taste.
Cook until done.
Add Gravy Master.
Mix cornstarch to water and add to stew.
Serve with bread and butter.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones.
Combine all ingredients; shape into patties.
Brown in a frying pan on both sides in hot oil until brown.
Can be served in bun with lettuce and tomato.

title: punch
directions: Mix grape juice as directed on can.
When ready to serve, add sherbet and Sprite.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil together in large bowl.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together and add to first ingredients.
Add squash and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour into 2 large greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagne provencal
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until al dente.
Drain.
Re-fill pot with cold water. Let noodles sit in water.
Heat oil or butter in a 10-inch frypan on medium heat.
Saute onions, garlic, basil and tarragon. When onions begin to brown, add mushrooms and cook until tender.
In a large bowl, mix Ricotta and cottage cheeses, eggs, sauteed veggies, spinach, salt, pepper, nutmeg, Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.

title: apple nut pudding cake with rum sauce
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and put into a 2 x 9 x 4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or grease and flour a Bundt pan. Bake.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.

Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake, then sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.
Yield:
One 3-layer cake.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Bake in 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: taco pie(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place baking sheet on middle shelf of oven.
Crumble beef into a large skillet.
Add onion and saute over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain off fat. Stir in water and seasoning mix.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf patties
directions: Mix ground beef with salt, pepper, onion and dry oatmeal and 1 egg thoroughly.
Make patties and lay in casserole dish with sides touching.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Turn over after 15 to 20 minutes of cooking.
Test for doneness.
If they are done, (not pink or bloody inside), drain off excess grease. Carefully open up one can of tomato soup and spread over meat patties.
Place in oven again to cook sauce.
Turn oven off.
Heat from oven is hot enough as it is.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Layer in casserole in order listed. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Cook meat in a skillet until brown and tender.
Drain off fat. Combine meat and onions with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimento, salt and a dash of pepper. Mix well.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until hot.
Trim with green pepper rings, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute rice, stirring often in oil until brown in large frying pan.
Stir in onions.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup crumbs; mix remaining ingredients.
Place in
9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: plain rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well. Beat in softened yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and shape into rolls.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken with sour cream, chillies, 1 can soup and 1-1/2 cups cheese.
Spoon 1/10 of filling down center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam-side down, in greased deep 9x13-inch baking pan.
Stir remaining can of soup to soften.
Spread over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate-sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with electric mixer, about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, 1 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread onto crust.
Boil 1 cup water and add 1 cup sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Take off stove and mix with peach jello.
Cool, then add peaches.
Spread onto second layer.

title: hamburger-squash casserole
directions: Brown the beef in a skillet with the onion.
Prepare the squash and drain.
Layer beef, squash, soup and cheese in a baking dish.
Season beef and squash with salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mash the potatoes, shortening, eggs and sugar.
Scald the milk; let cool.
Add milk to potato mixture.
Add flour and salt.
Mix with a spoon until you can handle without it sticking to your hands.
Let rise to double in size.
Push down.
Make rolls.
Let rise to double in size.
Refrigerate until ready to make out rolls.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook chicken in plenty of liquid.
Remove from bones and mix all ingredients.
Mix eggs with rice to prevent sticking together. Chicken should be torn in pieces. Bake in shallow pan in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Serve in squares with gravy made from remaining broth.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all together.
Cook for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes.

title: peppermint candy cookies
directions: Cream together margarine or butter, powdered sugar and vanilla; cream well.
Gradually add flour and walnuts.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: strawberry pops
directions: You will need 8 (5 ounce) paper cups.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in onion, rice, beef broth, 1 soup can water and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and pimento. Heat thoroughly.

title: janet's kosher dill pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, water and canning salt to boil; lower heat and fill jars that are packed with cucumbers.
Wash cucumbers.
Pack sterilized screw top jars with garlic, dill seed and alum.
Fill with hot vinegar, water and canning salt mixture and seal.

title: polenta and sausages
directions: Bring water to boil in a large saucepan with a generous pinch of salt.
Sprinkle in cornmeal, stirring constantly, with a wooden spoon.
Cook for 40 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine cauliflower, ham and mushrooms.
Melt oleo; stir in flour.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Mix with previous mixture and place in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and add an additional tablespoon of melted oleo on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent taco pie
directions: Press rolls together in a pie plate.
Cover the crust with chips.
Follow the directions for preparing the taco seasoning mix with the hamburger and onion.
Put this mixture on top of the chips.
Top with some of the diced tomatoes, several dollops of sour cream and then the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Garnish with the lettuce, tomatoes and salsa before serving.
For guests, put the garnishes in separate bowls and let them choose what they wish.
More sour cream and black olives could be other optional garnishes.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients, except oil.
Blend until smooth.
Add oil; blend again.
Makes approximately 3/4 cup.

title: jeanne's lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add to lima beans and add soup.
Flavor with salt and pepper and Lea & Perrins sauce.
Add artichokes.
Heat at 350° for 1/2 hour or until thoroughly hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lucy's biscuits(tennessee ridge)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
In a large bowl, put 4 cups of flour and baking soda.
Cut in lard until it looks like coarse crumbs.
Mix together remaining 1 cup of flour with buttermilk.
Add yeast mixture.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to flour and mix well.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead.
Place in a well-greased bowl, covered, in refrigerator.
Biscuits are ready to bake at any time.
When ready to bake, roll and cut as many as you want.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Yields around 3 dozen biscuits.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Break graham crackers into parts.
Place on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar. Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening with pastry blender until the size of peas.
Mix together vinegar, egg and water, then add to flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until moist.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic.
Add spaghetti sauce and next 6 ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and tomatoes. Boil until done.

title: peanut brittle mousse
directions: Add peanut brittle, vanilla and sugar to whipped cream; toss gently.
Place into mold and freeze.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large pan, brown ground beef and drain. Add remaining ingredients without draining. Cook about 1 hour and serve.

title: waldorf astoria beef stew
directions: Put vegetables and meat in roaster in layers.
Sprinkle on seasonings and tapioca.
Add tomato juice and water.
Cover roaster and cook in oven for 5 hours at 250°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a glass baking dish.
Distribute evenly in dish the graham cracker crumbs, butterscotch and chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Dribble over top 1 can Eagle Brand milk evenly. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool and cut.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat soups, Ro-Tel and broth in saucepan.
Place chicken and chips in layer.
Pour sauce over layers.
Sprinkle on onion, then cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: banana punch
directions: *When serving, mix in small amounts so that it will stay slushy.

title: potato bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all together.
Top with crushed chips or cereal.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer balls cookies
directions: Combine wafers and milk.
Add nuts and chips and mix well. Form into balls.
Roll in crushed wafers and coconut, then refrigerate.

title: homemade buttermilk
directions: Mix milk in very warm water until completely dissolved.
Pour into gallon jug and finish filling with warm water.
Let set out in warm room until thickened, usually 1 day and night.
When thickened, refrigerate.
Sometimes water will separate from milk; that's okay.
Just stir before using in bread or favorite recipe.

title: chicken breasts with dried beef
directions: Make roll with chicken breasts.
Wrap dried beef around it. If
one
slice won't go around, use a second one.
Secure with
2 wooden toothpicks.
Arrange in baking dish;
usually a 9 x 13-inch flat casserole will fit.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over it.
Bake at 280° for 3 hours uncovered.
Can be assembled ahead
and
kept refrigerated covered, also reheats nicely.
(This is
delicious
and
worked
great
at a recent progressive dinner
since
it
didn't
have to be watched and baked while I visited the other stops. - M.E.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into an 8 x 8-inch cake pan until it is at least half filled.

Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Melt oleo. Add oats, brown sugar and flour. Spread over apples. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. This is best with fresh apples but can also be used with frozen apples.

title: chicken a la simon and garfunkle
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme.
Place chicken breasts in a casserole dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and add white wine.
Bake for 30 minutes more.
Remove and lay slices of Mozzarella (or sprinkle grated) over the chicken.
Put it back in the oven just long enough for cheese to melt.
Serve over white rice.
Use the sauce to pour over chicken and rice.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together; roll.
Cut and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ethel's fudge frosting
directions: Bring to a rapid boil the first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix and spread over cool cake while icing is hot.

title: meal-in-one beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, in hot shortening, saute onion and chuck until lightly browned, stirring occasionally with a fork.
Add salt, pepper, dill seed and mushroom soup mix.
Stir in 1 cup hot water until well blended, then add corn, mixed vegetables and sour cream.
Spoon mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle Rice Chex evenly over top.
Bake 30 minutes, or until hot, covering loosely with foil after 15 minutes to prevent overbrowning of cereal.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Last, add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll out and cut in favorite shapes; be creative!
(Note:
Use powdered sugar to flour your cutting board; it works better than flour.) Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies with chocolate topping
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour to mixture alternately with milk. Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: rich 'n charlies italian salad
directions: Combine olive oil, Parmesan cheese, sugar and red wine vinegar.
Add sliced onion, chopped palm, chopped artichokes and pimento.
Stir.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Rinse and drain lettuce.
Tear into bite sized pieces.
Combine all and toss just before serving.

title: beef stew
directions: Flour beef cubes.
In a pan or Dutch oven, brown beef cubes in hot oil.
Place browned cubes in bottom of an electric crockery. Layer onions, potatoes, carrots and celery.
Sprinkle bouillon granules, basil and thyme.
Pour 2 cups water and beef stew mix over meat.
Cover and cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Heat cheese spread, chocolate and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is melted.
Gradually add sugar to chocolate mixture, beating with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Smooth surface.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: lemon whip freezer dessert
directions: Combine egg whites, milk, powder and water; beat until stiff peaks form.
In a separate bowl, mix egg yolks, sugar, lemon peel and juice.
Add slowly to whipped mixture, continuing to whip. Place in freezer until frozen.
(This may be put in serving dishes to freeze until served.)
Garnish with orange peel and a sprig of mint, or curled chocolate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pilgrim's pride apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9-inch pan.
Put apple filling in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle mixture over apple filling.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: harvest moon(indian dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Boil spaghetti, drain and set it aside in a roasting pan.
Stir together milk, butter and pepper on medium heat.
Continue to stir until boiling.
Pour sauce over noodles in roasting pan.
Fry up bacon crisp, drain and pat grease from bacon.
