Add to roasting pan.
Add tomatoes, cheese and corn. After adding all this to roasting pan, stir it together.
At 250°, bake for 1 or 2 hours, stirring every 20 or 30 minutes until cheese is melted.
Eat hot or cold.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together, then add beaten eggs.
Add melted margarine to sugar/flour mixture.
Add spices, butter flavoring and vanilla.
Stir in chopped apples.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at high, beat together the butter, cocoa and milk until smooth.
Gradually beat in the powdered sugar until right consistency.
Be sure cake is cool when frosting.

title: green jello salad
directions: Bring sugar and pineapple juice to a boil.
Add dissolved lemon and lime jellos.
Chill.
Mix crushed pineapple with cream cheese and milk.
Chill until ice cold.
Whip.
Then add jello and cream cheese mix.
Pour in large dish.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, bananas and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Put it in loaf pans.
Cook at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: one piece dinner with pork chops
directions: In a small roaster, layer peas, carrots, potatoes and onion. Season each layer with salt and pepper and dot with oleo.
Top with pork chops.
Top pork chops with tomatoes.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Take cover off and brown 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, cumin and red pepper.
Stir in chicken. Spoon 1/3 cup of the chicken mixture into each tortilla; roll up.

Place, seam side down, in 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Pour salsa over filled tortillas; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes; sprinkle with cilantro. Serve over hot cooked rice with chopped red peppers, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dieters french toast
directions: Beat eggs slightly with milk and salt in shallow bowl.
Dip bread slices one at a time into egg mixture, turning to coat both sides well.
Saute slowly in half the butter, turning once and adding remaining butter as needed.
Cut in half; drizzle with honey.
Yields 4 servings; 275 calories per serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into greased casserole and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it spins a thread. Remove from fire and add 1/2 the syrup to beaten egg whites. Place remainder of syrup on fire and cook until it forms a hard ball.
Add slowly to first mixture and beat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan or dry by spoonfuls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain off water.
Add soup, butter, milk and salt.
Fold gently until all is mixed together.
Put 1/2 of this in casserole and add layer of cheese.
Add the remainder of potato mixture and top with cheese.
Put in oven on low heat until cheese has melted.
Fold potatoes lightly so as not to mash them.

title: washboard cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together, then add shortening.
Mix well. Dissolve soda in hot water and add to above.
Add vanilla, salt and sifted flour.
Amount of flour needed varies with type of flour and size of eggs used.
Mix thoroughly and mold into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mildew remover
directions: Mix equal parts of nonsudsing household ammonia, dishwashing liquid and water.
Put in spray bottle.
Wash clothes immediately after spraying.

title: kraut kasserole
directions: Combine soup and mayonnaise.
Add half of soup mixture to hamburger, caraway seed and kraut.
Put in a baking dish.
Stir remaining soup mixture into potatoes.
Spread on top of meat and kraut mixture.

title: chicken verona
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the butter (careful not to burn). Add the finely chopped garlic buds and turn the heat to very low. Pound the chicken breasts until thin.
Cut the breasts into bite size pieces and set aside.

title: butter toffee
directions: You will need a candy thermometer.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat to a boil.
Marinate chicken 6 to 24 hours.
Top grilled chicken with grilled pineapple slices. Will marinate up to 8 boneless, skinless chicken breasts.

title: pineapple macadamia nut ice cream
directions: Cut top, bottom and sides off pineapple; slice and cut into bite size pieces.
Place 2 to 3 slices worth of pieces in bottom of a large bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Continue to layer pineapple and sugar until all pineapple is used.
Add the butter-glazed and the fresh nuts.
Mix all together and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Put the half and half in a large bowl; add the heavy cream, shaken well.
Gradually add the beaten eggs, vanilla, salt and almond flavoring.
Add to pineapple mixture; stir well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze according to the freezer's directions.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: *May use bacon, sausage or ham (cooked), chopped onions, tomatoes, diced potatoes (browned in bacon grease).

title: teske's tomato-less jambalaya
directions: Brown the chicken.
Drain the excess fat.
Add both types of onions and the bell pepper.
Saute until clear.
Add the chicken broth, garlic, sausage, ham and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add rice and bring the mixture to a slow boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Cook on low for 15 minutes (45 minutes if using brown rice).

title: creamed onions and carrots
directions: In saucepan, cook celery in butter until tender.
Blend in soup and sour cream.
Add wine and parsley.
Cut carrot halves in 2-inch pieces.
Add carrots and onions to soup mixture.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Moisten bread with water.
Press out and discard excess water. Set aside.
Saute onions, peppers and
celery in shortening until lightly browned.
Combine bread, sauteed vegetables, beef, eggs and seasonings.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Avoid overmixing if using mixer.
Shape into 1 big loaf and place in oven for about 1 hour.
Remove excess fat and liquid during cooking period.
Cool slightly.
Cut in about 13 slices per loaf.

title: polish hot beet relish(servings:  8)
directions: Heat cooked, shredded beets in melted butter in saucepan. Stir in flour, sugar and salt.
Add sour cream and vinegar.
Heat thoroughly, stirring frequently, but do not boil.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla. Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beans and franks
directions: Brown franks and onion.
Add beans and remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: marvelous mustard ribs(very good!)
directions: In small bowl, combine sugar, pepper, paprika, curry powder and salt. Rub ribs, coating well.
Place ribs in shallow pan. Cover and chill 2 to 6 hours. In a covered grill on low, place ribs, fat side up. Grill about 1 1/4 hours or until tender, turning once in awhile.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Pull bread into pieces and put into the following mixture of milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon to taste.
Mix well.
Sprinkle cinnamon or sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake slowly for about an hour at 325° or so.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of medium casserole; top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayo, sour cream and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Can be doubled, use 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Cut up and roll into corn meal in which the salt has been added.
Fry in hot oil or bacon drippings; stir frequently.
When golden brown, take out with spoon with holes and drain on paper towel.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to mashed potatoes.
Mix well.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Crumble topping on top.
Bake at 350° for 25-35 minutes, until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs which have been beaten.
Sift and measure flour; add dry ingredients to flour and sift again. Combine flour, nuts and apples to oil mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: amish moist apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix with spoon and let stand 48 hours before using.
Keep batter in refrigerator for 6 weeks (covered).
Use as needed. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as on box.
Let chill for 1 hour.
Mix all ingredients.
Let chill.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn if necessary.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter; pour over pretzels with sugar on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool; break with a knife.
Place in the bottom of a long bowl.

title: fudge topping
directions: Boil all ingredients for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool and spoon over ice cream.
Add peanuts, if desired.
Return to freezer.
Serve with whipped cream and a cherry.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, raisings and onion. In a small bow., combine the mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar.
pour over broccoli mixture; toss to coat.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno-pepper jelly
directions: Microwave Method:
Put jelly in 4-cup glass measure.
Microwave uncovered on High 3 to 4 minutes until melted, stirring once.
Add peppers and vinegar; microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until bubbling.
Pour into 3 hot, clean 6 ounce jars, dividing peppers equally among them.
Cover loosely and refrigerate 1 hour or until jelly has partially set.
Stir to distribute peppers evenly. Cover tight and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/3 cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the pineapple over entire bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump the cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Dump the entire box of dry cake mix evenly over, then slice margarine evenly over top.
Sprinkle nuts on last and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: minute tapioca ham loaf
directions: Ground together the ham and pork.
Mix tapioca through ground meat.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 7 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan (or form a loaf and bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan) at 450° for 20 minutes.
Decrease temperature to 375° and bake 45 minutes longer.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: herb-tomato beef kabobs
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Preheat broiler.
Place kabobs on unheated rack; broil 4 to 5 inches from heat, 8 minutes for medium rare to 12 minutes for well done.
Turn; brush with mixture often.
Or, grill kabobs on uncovered grill directly over hot coals, turning and basting often.

title: diet jello salad
directions: Prepare jello according to box directions and refrigerate. When nearly set, stir in fresh vegetables.
Return to refrigerator until set.
Best if eaten within 2 days.

title: fried chicken
directions: Peel off skin of chicken; roll in flour.
Fry until brown in corn oil.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook and debone chicken breasts. Cook and drain noodles.
Combine soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Spread noodles in buttered baking dish.
Layer the rest.
Top with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put into regular graham cracker crust or vanilla wafer crust.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and soda; let set.
Mix butter, cocoa and water together in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil and pour over dry mix.
Mix together 2 minutes at medium speed buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend into other ingredients.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool cake.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine dry ingredients in pan.
Stir in milk until smooth. Add margarine.
Bring slowly to boil, stirring.
Boil 1 minute. Off heat, stir in cheese until melted, then macaroni.
Pour into buttered casserole; top with crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Chop onion and cut bacon into small pieces.
Brown ground sirloin, bacon and onion in skillet.
Drain off excess grease. Place in 3-quart casserole dish.
Drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Do not drain pork and beans.
Add all beans and the rest of the ingredients to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunlight carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Stir in coconut, carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool; frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pineapple dream pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar in bowl. Fold in whipped topping and crushed pineapple. Spoon into pie crust.
Top with pineapple chunks. Chill 2 hours or overnight. Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: chocolate homemade ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand.
Add chocolate milk.
Freeze.

title: chinese pork roast
directions: Combine all ingredients except the meat and mix well.
Pour mixture over the meat and marinate overnight.
Place meat in a roasting pan.
Bake covered at 350° for about 3 hours or until done.
Serve with rice.

title: country vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil. Cook vegetables, parsley and garlic 3 minutes or just until vegetables begin to cook. Add broth and bay leaves; heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Return broth to boiling.
Stir in uncooked noodles. Boil, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until noodles are tender. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 8.

title: apple rings
directions: Mix in baking dish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: chicken-n-biscuits
directions: Put soup in bottom of cake pan.
Stir in cooked chicken.
Top with unbaked biscuits until top is covered.
Bake at temperature as directed on biscuits.
Serve hot!

title: fruit salad in a hurry
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip and pour in oblong container (8 x 12-inch).
Ice top with Cool Whip.

title: garden skillet
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini and onion with basil in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts; stir occasionally.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Cream sugars, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add buttermilk mixture with sugar mixture alternately with flour.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.

title: yummy surprise
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, walnuts and margarine.
Press into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, reserving 1 tablespoon for garnish. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Cool completely.

title: banana and orange smoothy
directions: Puree the banana, orange juice or orange and grapefruit juices, ice and lemon juice in a blender.
Pour into a tall glass and enjoy.

title: yummasetti
directions: Mix all the soup and cream together and pour over the other ingredients which have been put in a large container.
Mix.
Pour into roaster or large pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last half hour, put bread crumbs over the top and bake uncovered.

title: baked onions
directions: Cut off root end and place in a Pam sprayed glass (ovenproof) dish.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
When done, remove outer husk and season to taste.

title: beans trio
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain and set aside.
In a large baking dish, combine beans, sugar, catsup, mustard, vinegar and peppers.
Add ground beef mixture and mix well. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put everything into blender and mix for 1 minute.
Pour into a well-greased pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer in 3-quart serving bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 13-inch baking dish and spread apple pie filling on bottom.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons water.
Layer in the following order:
coconut, cake mix and pecans.
Slice 2 sticks margarine over this and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Can be served warm with whipped cream or cooled.

title: fried artichokes
directions: Sprinkle artichoke hearts with salt and pepper.
Mix parsley with bread crumbs.
Beat eggs slightly.
Dip hearts in egg; roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil about 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve very hot.
Serves 6 people.

title: impossible chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix the chicken, peas and carrots, mushrooms and onion in plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds with blender or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: delma's wedding punch
directions: Heat all together (except ginger ale) in a large sauce pan until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat; cool. Divide into 4 equal batches; freeze. When ready to use, thaw slightly until slushy. The night before, put ginger ale in freezer. By the next morning, the ginger ale should be slightly frozen (slushy). Add 3 (2 liter size) bottles ginger ale to each batch of punch base. This recipe will make about 7 gallons of punch or 147 servings.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Mix bread in a large bowl and toss with salt, pepper and herbs.
Add cooked vegetables, eggs and water chestnuts.
Moisten with chicken broth, using enough to make dressing, which is neither dry or soggy.
If any dressing will be cooked separately, make moister and bake along with the turkey the last hour of cooking.
Makes about 12 cups or enough to stuff a 10 to 12 pound turkey and bake some on the side.

title: beef noodles casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion until tender; drain and set aside.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add meat, soup, milk, salt and pepper to noodles.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed.
Combine all ingredients except butter.
Mix well, form into tiny balls and fry in butter on low heat.
Shake pan to brown evenly.
Yields: 48 meat balls.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter; mix in cheese and flour combined.
(In blender, mix 1/4 at a time.)
Roll out thin and either cut into sticks about 4 inches long and 1/2 inch wide or into 1-inch rounds.
Bake at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cottage cheese, blending well.
Stir in grapes and pineapple. Fold in whipped topping.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight before serving.

title: jellied raspberry cranberry salad ring
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chill until syrupy.
Add sour cream and cranberry. Pour into mold and chill to set.

title: oven scramble strata
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Put in oblong baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches that has been sprayed with Pam.
Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour over ham, bread, etc. mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot. Serves 12 or more.
Serve muffins with this and it makes a very nice combination.

title: lite sweet potato fruit salad
directions: Place potatoes and fruit in a large bowl; mix together.
Mix all other ingredients in a smaller bowl and pour over sweet potatoes and fruit to coat.
Chill before serving.

title: noodles parmesan
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Melt margarine and blend in remaining ingredients.
Toss with hot noodles.

title: shelly's magic buns
directions: Separate rolls.
Take marshmallows.
Dip in butter, roll in sugar mixture and wrap in crescent roll.
Make sure there are no openings in roll by pinching shut.
Roll completed crescent roll in sugar mixture.
Place roll in muffin cup and tin.
Bake for about 13 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften in a bowl. Chop green onions and mix in cream cheese. Add Worcestershire sauce and chipped beef (torn into small pieces) to mixture. Work it together and form a ball. Refrigerate for about 2 hours before serving.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Make 1 box strawberry jello and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan to set up.
When firm, dissolve the lemon jello in the boiling water.
Mix in the cream cheese until smooth and add the crushed pineapple and juice.
Chill until thick enough to put on top of the strawberry layer without melting it. (If you pour it over a large spoon, it does not make a hole when you pour.)
When the second layer is set firm, make the second box of strawberry jello and chill until thick enough to put on top of the pineapple layer without melting it.
When completely set, cut into squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add vegetables and squash to crumbs.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add 1 cup water.
Add 1 beaten egg, salt and poultry seasoning to taste.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased) 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook and stir onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk and egg.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle evenly over corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: relief society potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes the day before (whole with peels).
Cut potatoes in small pieces and put in large bowl.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and soup.
Stir together.
Add green onions and sour cream and mix well.
Stir mixture into potatoes and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Melt the 4 tablespoons margarine; add in cornflakes.
Stir gently to coat.
Place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add peaches and juices.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes with a hand mixer and then beat in butter, eggs, salt and pepper.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Make a deep well in the center of the potatoes.
Put the cheese into the center of the potatoes and press it down firmly.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: persimmons pudding(steamed)
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, sugar, egg and milk. Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add butter and nuts. Combine persimmon and flour mixtures. Turn into a well-greased mold with a lid. If no lid is available, cover tightly with foil. Place on rack in kettle. Fill kettle with water halfway up mold. Cover and steam for 2 hours. Unmold on serving platter. Flame with warmed brandy, if desired, and serve with Hard Sauce. Makes 8 servings.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Cook or steam chicken.
Bone and cut into bite-sizes.
Dip tortilla chips in leftover broth.
Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer chicken, chopped onion, 1/2 cup of soup, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Repeat.
Top with grated cheese and cover with Ro-Tel.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spicy.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Mix cracker crumbs and cheese together.
Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Mix soup, water and sour cream.
Pour some soup mixture into bottom of casserole dish.
Put in chicken. Add remainder of soup mixture over top. Sprinkle remainder of cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat quick barbecue ground turkey bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground turkey and 1/2 cup of onion until brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Stir baking mix, milk and egg substitute until blended.
Pour over ground turkey mixture. Sprinkle with remaining onion.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook together hamburger, onions, pepper and tomato sauce. Cook 1 large package egg dumplings; separate and drain.
Put dumplings in pan.
Put meat mixture on top of dumplings.
Add cheese and let it melt in oven.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in margarine over low heat.
Add beef and cook, stirring until beef is brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes, add sour cream and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil on moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes or to soft boil stage.
Remove from heat and beat until begins to hold its shape.
Stir in nuts and cherries and quickly pour in oiled pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Prepare the night before using.
Cook sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, milk and Pet milk slightly.
Add sausage, bread cubes and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: oven fried squash
directions: Using only small amount of cooking spray, spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat to 450°.
Beat eggs and water in a bowl and set aside.
Mix corn meal, salt and pepper.
Dip sliced squash in egg solution and then roll in corn meal.
Place one layer in baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes, then turn with a spatula.
Bake 20 more minutes.
The squash should be golden brown.

title: cream of taco
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain, then add other ingredients.
Cook until well blended; pour over chips.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Arrange corn chips over bottom of lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole. Spread chili over chips.
Slice tamales over chili. Top with cheese slices.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Dissolve morsels in top of double boiler.
Don't overcook less than 5 minutes.
Mix with peanuts and noodles.
Drop onto wax paper and let set until cooled.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, celery and onion.
Toss until well blended. Chill.

title: sausage squares
directions: Cook sausage and drain off ALL grease.
Combine with rest of ingredients (except bread).
Place over heat to melt cheese.
Place bread slices in casserole dish.
Spoon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carne guisada
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Trim all fat.
Brown steak until well done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add pepper(s) and onion.
Saute.
In a separate skillet, brown flour and add water to form gravy.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with refried pinto beans, Spanish rice and flour tortillas.

title: frozen peach dessert
directions: In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients; pour on top of crust.
Spread with extra graham crackers, then freeze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar and shortening; add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Add all dry ingredients gradually.
Add raisins and nuts at end.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: quick fluffy frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep small mixer bowl.
Beat slowly until blended.
Increase speed and beat until mixture holds soft peaks, 4 to 6 minutes.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: chocolate frosted rice krispies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Turn down and add peanut butter. Stir until peanut butter is dissolved. Pour over Rice Krispies. Press into a 13 x 9 pan.

title: hash and corn bread
directions: Mix hash, onion and egg. Prepare muffin batter; add salt and cheese. Spread half the muffin batter in greased 8-inch square pan. Spread on hash mixture; top with remaining batter. Bake in 400° oven about 25 minutes. Cut in slices or squares. Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine mustard, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt.
Dip chicken in mixture then roll in flour.
After chicken is lightly coated, dip in the egg.
Roll in the crushed crackers.
Melt butter in sheet pan, then add chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 45 minutes or until center is not pink.

title: creamy italian sub sandwiches
directions: Mix dressing and Italian dressing.
Toss lettuce with 1/4 cup of the dressing mixture.
Brush cut surfaces of rolls with remaining dressing mixture.
Fill rolls with meat, cheese slices, vegetables and lettuce mixture.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: shrimp luncheon dish
directions: Melt the shortening in skillet on high heat. Add ingredients in order listed.
Place lid on skillet. When steaming freely, reduce to lowest heat and cook 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turnovers
directions: Work flour, yeast, shortening, butter, salt and sugar as for pie dough until well blended.
Beat eggs and milk together; add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out thin and cut into 5-inch circles.
Fill with your favorite pie filling.
Fold in half and seal edges.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Can be rolled in sugar before baking.)
Roll in powdered sugar while warm or glaze with powdered sugar frosting while still warm.
Dough may be frozen.
Makes 35 to 40 turnovers.
Nice recipe for bake sales.

title: linguine with tomatoes and cream
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add stewed tomatoes, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in milk and continue to simmer 5 more minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Good with carrots, celery sticks or pretzels.

title: layered crispy rice bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Melt margarine in baking pan in oven.
Sprinkle cereal evenly over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over cereal mixture.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over sweetened condensed milk.
Distribute chocolate pieces and butterscotch pieces evenly over top of mixture in baking pan.
Press lightly. Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute the onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in
olive oil for 2 minutes; add potatoes and vegetable stock and simmer over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Add corn kernels, milk and herbs; simmer for an additional 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Whisk for 1 minute; let rest 5 minutes.
Whisk again about 1 minute.
Pour over grated cabbage.

title: bean salad
directions: Put this mixture in a jar and shake well.
Pour the mixture over the ingredients; set aside.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or 7 to 8 hours.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: Prepare beans according to package directions.
In large pan, saute chopped onion in a little olive oil.
Add beans, spaghetti sauce and basil.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
At this point, you can freeze the bean mixture for use later.
In boiling, salted water, cook the ditalini.
Drain over bowl, being sure to save the water.
Combine bean mixture, macaroni and reserved water to make a soup as thick or soupy as you desire.

title: stove top potatoes
directions: Cook the onion in the oil and butter in a heavy skillet until just beginning to brown.
Stir in the vinegar and potatoes; pour in the boiling water.
Cover skillet and simmer, stirring once or twice, until they are done, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: amish coffee cake
directions: Mix the brown sugar and flour.
Cut in shortening until get little beads.
Reserve 1 cup for later.
Stir in egg and vanilla. Stir coffee and soda together; add to egg and flour mixture. Mixture may be a little lumpy.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle reserved cup of dry mix over batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: 1. Combine apples, sugar, and mix well. Add oil, nuts, eggs, and vanilla.
2. Blend shifted flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt.
Add to apple mix and blend.
3. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350°
for one hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and margarine well and pour into baking dish.
Add fruit of your choice.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until top of cobbler is brown.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain juice and remove bones from salmon.
Crumble crackers and add with egg to salmon.
Heat oil.
Mix ingredients well and shape into cakes.
Drop into hot oil and fry until golden brown on each side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomatoes, onion, pinto beans, cheese and soup.
Cook until cheese melts.
Pour over half the bag of Doritos in baking dish.
Bake at 320° for 20 minutes.

title: aggression cookies(good for kids to make on dreary days)
directions: Put everything into large bowl.
Mash, knead or beat with hands.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Butter bottom of glass. Place balls in ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip glass in sugar and lightly mash balls to flatten.
Re-dip glass in sugar each time. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: peach pan pie
directions: Bring water to a boil for a few seconds.
Add peaches and simmer while making pastry.
Line sides of baking dish with pastry.
Pour in peach mixture.
Cover top with pastry.
Make a slash in center of pastry.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Saute in butter until tender.
Mix crumbs together.
Layer into casserole dish as follows:
crumbs, onion, cheese, repeat layers.
Mix soup and milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes 20 servings.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add Ragu sauce and seasonings; cook for 15 minutes. Cook spinach as directed.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions.
In a large bowl, mix spinach with macaroni and cheese.
Beat the eggs and add to the mixture.
Add oil and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a 7 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Pour meat sauce over this and sprinkle lots of Parmesan cheese over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in oven, uncovered.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Cut off roots and tops of leeks.
Slice and wash.
In soup pot, saute leeks in oil and butter until limp.
Add potatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Combine sugar and 6 cups of water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add fruit juices and bananas.
Mix well. Freeze.
When ready to use, place fruit mixture in punch bowl. Allow to soften slightly.
Bread into slush.
Add 7-Up.
May tint with food coloring if desired.
Yields 25 servings.

title: potato bake
directions: Slice Tater Tots thin, grate cheese and dice onion.
Oil baking dish.
Line with Tater Tots on bottom layer.
Add cheese and onion.
Repeat process until dish is full.

title: chicken nachos - meets the four f's (fine finger football food)
directions: Rinse and cube the chicken breasts.
Add water, taco seasoning, Cajun seasoning, honey, red pepper and cubed chicken to skillet.
Bring contents to a boil; reduce to simmer.
Cook for 30 minutes, until sauce is slightly thickened.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Peel and brown onions
in bacon drippings.
Remove to a separate dish.
Saute beef	when brown and sprinkle flour over it. Add salt, pepper,	marjoram
and thyme.
Add bouillon and wine. Stir gently.
Cover
and simmer slowly in 275° oven for 3 1/2 hours
(just
barely bubbling occasionally).
After this return onions and mushrooms, sliced and cooked.
Stir and cook 3/4 hour longer, covered.
This
makes
thick brown sauce (add more bouillon if it's too dry as it cooks).

title: bedford bean soup
directions: *Beans:
Large limas, baby limas, navy, lentils, split peas, pinto, kidney, black-eyed peas.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl (or in Quick Shake), combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add in eggs and milk.
Mix together and let stand a few minutes. Cook in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain. Sprinkle
with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: banana punch
directions: Blend fruit juices and bananas.
Make a syrup of sugar and water.
Boil 5 minutes and cool.
Add fruit mixture to syrup. Freeze half of this mixture.

title: japanese raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 300° until done, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Prepare Kraft Dinner as directed.
Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Combine all ingredients; mix well and place in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans 3 times. Soak overnight with dry ingredients.
Add salt pork. Bake in a 325° oven for 8 hours. Add water as necessary.

title: last minute appetizer
directions: Cut cantaloupe into 4 equal parts.
Scoop out seeds and remove skins.
Season with salt and pepper; set aside.
Cut avocado in half and carefully remove pit.
Peel and slice each half into 4 equal pieces.
Immediately brush with lemon juice to prevent browning.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour, then serve.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water and 2 teaspoon salt and m.s.g.; simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool, then cut chicken into large bite size pieces.
Combine flour, onion powder, garlic powder, celery salt, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt with 1/2 cup chicken broth and poultry seasoning.
Mix until smooth.
Heat 3 cups chicken broth to boiling; add flour mixture.
Stir and cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened; add chicken and blend well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with margarine and cover with a biscuit crust. Make slits in crust and bake at 375° until browned (approximately 20 minutes).

title: caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of an ungreased Bundt pan with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons nuts in pan.
Add brown sugar and water to remaining margarine and heat to boil.
Remove from heat.
Separate biscuit dough.
Shape into balls.
Place half of dough in bottom of pan and pour half of sauce over balls. Repeat biscuits and sauce.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Invert immediately onto plate.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order: lettuce, green onion, celery, green pepper, frozen peas, hard-boiled eggs, bacon bits, 1 1/2 to 2 cups mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Seal with Saran Wrap and let stand overnight in fridge.

title: spider cider
directions: Combine cider, cloves, cinnamon sticks, thinly peeled rind of 4 lemons, 2 lemons, peeled and thinly sliced, and the nutmeg.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 15 minutes. Allow to cool; then strain.
Discard spices.
Chill overnight in refrigerator to allow flavors to blend.
Heat when ready to serve. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: kuchen bread(german potato bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in potato water.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and egg.
Stir with dough hook in mixer.
Add enough flour to make thick enough to knead.
Add raisins.
Turn onto floured board and knead for 5 minutes.
Divide in half and roll each half to 1-inch thick circle.
Place in greased pie pan.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let rise in refrigerator.

title: barbara's spanish rice
directions: Fry ground meat.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Bring to boil and add rice.
Lower heat and cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except onion.
Chill with whole onion in container at least overnight.
Can keep one month.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream together the powdered sugar and margarine.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix well until light and fluffy.
Spread this on the 2 crusts.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender. Bone and cut into pieces. Cook noodles in the chicken broth until done.

title: tuna salad with green beans and tomatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine tuna, green beans, tomatoes, onions and capers.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, whisk together red wine and balsamic vinegars, olive oil and thyme.
Add to the tuna mixture along with the arugula, watercress or spinach.
Toss gently.
Makes 2 servings as a main course or 4 servings as an appetizer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Keep about 1/2 of the liquid.
Combine with soup and add beans.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
When bubbly, cover with onions.
Return to oven and brown about 10 minutes more. Serves 8 to 10.

title: beefaroni
directions: Heat oil in deep non-stick skillet with lid.
Add onion and beef, raise heat to high; cook until brown (5 minutes).
Add pepper as chopped.
Stir in garlic.
Add chicken broth, spaghetti sauce and macaroni.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to cook at moderate boil until macaroni is done (about 10 minutes for al dente).
Serve at once with parmesan cheese.

title: mom's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and stir until mixed.
Stir in bananas and nuts, mixing well.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix all together and pour onto 2 ungreased cookie sheets.
Cut into 64 cookie bars or pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can frost with powdered sugar icing while still warm.
Anyone who likes gingerbread will love this recipe.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix butter with cake mix.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.

title: squash casserole
directions: Crush 12 crackers and put in casserole dish.
Add cooked squash with onions, cheese, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Crumble remaining 6 crackers on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake until brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices together and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together oil, sugar and eggs; add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; add buttermilk, soda, prunes and nuts.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
About 15 minutes before cake is done, prepare glaze. Pour hot glaze immediately over cake in pan.
When cool, remove.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour.
Brown, then add broth, milk and water mixed together.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add salt, rice, chicken and vegetables.
Pour in 11 x 18-inch glass pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; add remaining ingredients except Kisses.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a chocolate Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing lightly into cookie.
Let cookies stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: pistachio ambrosia
directions: Combine both cans of pineapple in a large bowl, including undiluted liquid.
Sprinkle pudding on top and do not mix.
Let sit for 3 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add onion.
Saute over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add water and chicken broth.
Heat and stir until dissolved.
Gradually add noodles and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Stir.
Add broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes. Add milk and cheese; continue to cook until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Makes 12 cups.

title: dar's spaghetti salad
directions: Drain noodles for at least one hour.
Chill after pouring dressing over noodles.
Dice up the vegetables.
Remove noodles from fridge and add all remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: sunday yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Cover and let stand 8 hr or overnight on kitchen counter. In morning turn out onto flour board and knead lightly. Roll 1/2 thick and cut into rolls, place rolls on greased cookie sheet. Let rise 4-6 hrs. Pre heat oven to 400° bake rolls 10-12 min.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in bowl and put dressing on. Refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Roast chicken and cut into cubes. Add celery and mandarin oranges.
Mix with mayonnaise. Serve on leaf lettuce. Sprinkle with cashew nuts and crumbled fried bacon.

title: scrambled egg with cheese
directions: Break egg into microproof bowl.
Add milk, shredded cheese and seasonings; blend together.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave oven at power level 6 for 1 minute.
Stir egg.
Cook in microwave oven at power level 6 for 1 1/2 additional minutes. Stir egg, let sit for 2 minutes, then serve.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from pan.
Add 2 teaspoons of prepared mustard.
Pour over potato salad while both potatoes and dressing are hot.
Mix well.
If more dressing is needed, add more Miracle Whip.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the combined dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: best ever tuna salad
directions: Remove shells from eggs. and combine with all other ingredients.
Add to cooled macaroni and mix well.
Better if made the day before.

title: zesty potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the potatoes, water, onion, garlic, salt and pepper, bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. (Do not drain). Mash potatoes in liquid almost smooth. Add remaining ingredients; cook and stir until the cheese is melted.

title: apple crisplincoln, nebraska
directions: Place sliced apples in 8-inch square glass pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake in microwave for 7 minutes on medium-high.
(Or bake in oven, pre-heated to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.)
Serve warm with ice cream or cream topping.
Yummy!
Makes 6 servings.

title: bermuda salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in jar.
Shake vigorously.
In a large bowl, combine cauliflower, onion rings and olives.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Cover; marinate several hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Toss with cheese and lettuce just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings (about 10 cups).

title: mamo's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and water. Roll out flat and press in pie pan. Makes about 2 pie crusts.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine and pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: apple cherry pie
directions: Pour pie fillings, sugar and water mixture into greased Pyrex dish.
Spread "prepared" cake mixture on top.
Cut up the butter over that.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cook at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In medium size bowl, combine ground beef, rice, onion, garlic, basil, salt and pepper.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
In a 4-quart pressure cooker pan, combine soup and water.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat.
Add meatballs to soup mixture.
Cover and heat to 15 pounds pressure.
Cook meatballs 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow pressure to reduce gradually.
When pressure is completely reduced, remove lid and serve meatballs immediately.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and form into balls.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix well and pour into tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°; grease pans well.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot, onion, celery, green pepper and tomato juice.
Cook until almost done.
Add bouillon cubes and lemon juice and cook until vegetables are done.
Add mushrooms, green beans and sweetener.

title: egg rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup of oil into a large pan. Add shredded cabbage, onions and carrots; simmer. Add 2 cups of water and stir; add soy sauce. Cook down until wilty. Salt and pepper vegetables. Add chopped or whole small shrimp. Mix 3 tablespoons cornstarch with water and add to vegetables. Cook until shrimp are tender; let cool. Roll in wrappers. Seal with beaten egg. Place on greased pan, not touching; freeze. Wrap individually in plastic wrap. Remove from freezer when needed and fry in small amount of oil until brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger, drain. Fry tortillas lightly in hot oil. Dip into enchilada and tomato sauce (mixed together). Place meat, onions and olives on tortillas, sprinkle with cheese. Roll and place in oiled baking dish, seam side down. Pour remaining sauce on top. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly (about 15 to 20 minutes). Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve immediately. Garnish each enchilada with shredded lettuce and hard cooked egg, if desired.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together well.
Add cream.
Mix well.
Cook on medium heat or in microwave and butter.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Cool.
May sprinkle top with cinnamon, if desired.
Good with fresh rhubarb added to pudding when being cooked, about 1 cup.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well
and
bake in a square cake pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: devil's eyes(pb cookies)
directions: Combine oleo, peanut butter and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Press center of each ball with thumb.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes. Press candy star into center of each cookie; continue baking 2 to 3 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: keftes de espinca
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly and cook in very little water (1 cup) for 5 minutes.
Drain well and chop.
Mix spinach with all ingredients except oil and set aside for 1/2 hour giving matzo meal time to absorb.
Form in round balls, press between palms and fry.
When patties are all fried, put in pan and cover over very low flame for 15 minutes with chicken stock.

title: cheese salad
directions: Warm pineapple juice and mix with cream cheese.
Add Miracle Whip.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add Cool Whip last. Refrigerate.

title: beef stick (salami)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate, covered, for 3 days.
Stir well once daily.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Simmer meatballs in sauce mixture for 20 minutes.

title: praline pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and pecans together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° until pie shell is golden brown and praline mixture is bubbly.
Remove from oven and set aside to cool. Add butterscotch pie filling to milk and mix until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with more Cool Whip on top if desired.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer.
Mix for 5 minutes.
Put paper cups in muffin pan.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of cup.
Fill 3/4 full with filling.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into graham cracker crust.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over cherries. Refrigerate.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium bowl. Cut in butter or margarine with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Add cheese. Toss until well blended. Sprinkle water over mixture and mix lightly with fork until pastry holds together and leaves the side of the bowl clean. Roll on a floured surface into a 12x10-inch rectangle. Cut in half lengthwise; then cut each half cross wise into 1/2 inch strips. Lift strips one at a time, twist and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until lightly golden. Cool before serving. Makes 4 dozen.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in chafing dish over hot water.
Cover and heat. Top dip with chopped, toasted almonds.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli; break into small pieces.
Put vegetables in bowl.
Combine other ingredients, except bacon, and pour on vegetables.
Toss gently.
Garnish with bacon.
Chill several hours.
Serve cold.

title: lemon or lime chiffon pie
directions: Stir together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Cool until set.

title: country style steak
directions: Take cube steak, pour Worcestershire sauce over while tenderizing with a fork.
After meat is tenderized, roll in flour and place in crock-pot.
Add soup and milk.
Use flour to thicken to desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Start on low before you go to work and will be done when you get home.

title: dill pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in clear water; drain. Pack in jar with dill, pepper and garlic. Bring to a boil salt, turmeric powder, alum, vinegar and water. Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: caramel pie
directions: The pie shell may be prepared while the condensed milk is cooking.
Put the unopened can of milk into a large enough saucepan to be able to cover it entirely with water, leaving a good inch of water over the top of the can.
Start with lukewarm water, with the can in the water, and bring to a slow boil.
Maintain a gentle boil for two hours.
Warning:
Do not let the water boil down to the level of the can or boil out of the pot!
Since the can is sealed, if the water level falls, the contents of the can will be heated enough to cause it to explode if this happens.
However, as long as the can is covered by water, the temperature will go no higher than the boiling water which is 212°.

title: cheerwine punch
directions: At time of serving, mix Cheerwine and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and sherbet to taste.

title: cucumber salad
directions: You will need a small mixing bowl.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients. Process until smooth.
Makes 2 (8 oz) servings.

title: cherry cheese salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with cherry juice.
Add cherries, pineapple and marshmallows. Stir in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and chop.
Combine chopped stems, cheese, margarine and onions.
Fill mushroom caps with the mixture.
Broil 2 or 3 minutes or until top of filling is lightly brown.
Serve hot.

title: ham rolls
directions: Finely chop ham.
Remove rolls intact from package and slice in half.
Mix next 5 ingredients together.
Spread butter mixture on both top portion and bottom portion of rolls. Sprinkle bottom portion of rolls with chopped ham and top with cheese.
Place top layer of rolls on top of ham and cheese layer. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut or pull rolls apart and serve warm.

title: fruit cup
directions: Mix and press into square pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken pastry turnover
directions: Let frozen bread dough thaw until pliable (overnight in refrigerator is an easy way).
Combine all remaining ingredients. Cut loaf of bread dough into 8 equal slices.

Using a little flour on board and rolling pin, pat and roll dough into 5-inch circles. Place filling in strip lengthwise down center of dough circles. Pull dough edges up and pinch together to form a ridge across top. Place, smooth side down, on a greased baking sheet.
Prick several times with fork to vent for steam.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until well browned.
Makes 8.

title: oriental dip
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: finger gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 of soda.
Heat the remaining soda slightly.
Add to softened gelatin.
Pour into a square pan. Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken crescents
directions: In a medium bowl, mix the cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add milk, salt, pepper, onion, chives and mushrooms. Stir in chicken.
Mix well and set aside.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and kidney beans.
While this cooks, chop lettuce and tomatoes and grate cheese.
In chip bag, crush chips.
Right before eating, mix burger mixture, chopped vegetable mixture, crushed chips and Thousand Island dressing.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Alternate, starting and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes a very delicious crusty cake.
Take out of pan as soon as done.
Preheat oven and don't look at it until almost done.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients, milk and yeast.
Knead, roll out and cut like biscuits.
Let rise 5 minutes.
Bake at 475° (watch for your own choice of brownish coloring) about 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated and pinched off at each meal.
Let stand (rise) 5 or 10 minutes.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate 3 layers of tortillas, meat sauce and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Pour 1/8 cup water at each edge of pan. Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (or in microwave for 10 to 11 minutes).
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine in large bowl, cottage cheese, butter, a mixture of sugar, salt and soda, onion, dill seed, egg and softened yeast.
Beat well to blend.
Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: pasta e fageol
directions: Brown garlic lightly in olive oil in saucepot. Add tomatoes, onions and your preferred blend of seasonings. Simmer several hours, adding water as needed. Add beans. Cook 1 more hour. Cook ditalini al dente. Partly drain. Add to rest just before serving.

title: pineapple bread
directions: De-crust and cube bread.
Saute bread in margarine.
Mix in bowl the eggs, sugar and flour.
Stir in pineapple.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until tender; drain.
Brown onion and carrots in frypan with butter.
Combine zucchini, carrots, onion, stuffing and hamburger and stir well.
Mix sour cream and soup well and mix with the rest.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, cheese and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and mix well.
Add milk and mix until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously by hand 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix melted butter and 1 teaspoon garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand 20 minutes, then blend remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
It can be baked in 2 loaf pans or 1 large angel food pan.
Ummmmm.
So good with whipped cream.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Bottom:
Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon vegetables
directions: Arrange potatoes and carrots in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 8 minutes.
Add yellow squash and zucchini.
Cover and steam 2 minutes, or until crisp-tender. Place vegetables in serving bowl.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients; pour mixture over vegetables, tossing gently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Combine baking soda, flour, sugar and butter (cut into small pieces) to make crumbs.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish or pan. Save 1 1/2 cups crumbs for top.
Put cherries on top of crumbs. Top with the 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
(Pan is better to bake in.)
Cut into squares.

title: carrot bread
directions: Grease and flour one large or two small bread pans.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add the eggs one at a time and beat until thick and creamy.
Add soda, baking powder, salt, spices and beat well to blend.
Add one cup of flour and mix in well.
Add grated carrots and the other 1/2 cup flour.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in casserole dish and shake dry French onion soup over so all pieces are well covered.
Place, well covered, in refrigerator.
Leave a minimum of 4 hours, but better if left 8 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Finish
baking
at 350°.	When a silver knife stuck in within an inch of center comes out clean, it is done. Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy baked steak
directions: Brown steak pieces in a small amount of oil.
Add soups and cans of water.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.
Thicken gravy with flour and water.
Also makes great beef and noodles.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper. Add ketchup, mustard and brown sugar. Mix well.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Boil ham in water.
Add 1/2 cup margarine.
Salt to taste. While ham is cooking, make dumplings.
Mix like making biscuits. Roll out real thin and cut in squares.
Drop into boiling ham.
Put in large baking dish and drop eggs around in this.
Roll out top for crust and put on top.
Place 1/2 cup margarine on top of crust. Bake in oven until brown at 450°.
If too thick, add a little milk.

title: country breakfast special(microwave recipe)
directions: Heat potatoes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes; peel and slice. Meanwhile in 9-inch baking dish, heat butter, green pepper and onion 3 to 4 minutes on High until vegetables are tender; add sliced potatoes.

title: chicken, ham and bacon bundles
directions: Place each half chicken breast on ham slice. Wrap in a slice of bacon and secure with toothpicks.

Place bundles in baking dish. With wire whisk, stir soup or soups well until smooth and pour over chicken bundles, covering completely. Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 2 1/2 hours or until golden brown on top.
Serve with rice, noodles, etc.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together and add enough milk so pancakes spread out nicely in pan. Fry until brown and crisp. Serve warm with applesauce, maple syrup or honey.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer potatoes (skin on), onions, garlic salt, pepper, sausage and cheese.
Cover with greased foil (eliminates sticking).
Bake at 375° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Beat ingredients, following Solomon's instructions with Proverbs 23:14.
Makes 2 loaf cakes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Pour over 1st mixture.
Put 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate overnight if you wish.

title: 15 minute cheese pie
directions: Combine
crumbs,
tablespoons of sugar and oleo, and press into bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Mix in mashed bananas and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into banana mixture.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Simmer onions and
celery
in butter until tender.
Add to corn bread, white
bread, eggs, sage, salt and pepper.
Mix well, adding broth as
needed.
Stuff
in
turkey. May bake in pan in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: roasted carrot and beet soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place carrots, celery and onion in a shallow oven proof dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with the sugar, ginger and mace.
Pour 2 c. of broth into the bottom of the dish.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours. Remove vegetables from the oven and transfer them along with any liquid, to a large pot.
Add 4 c. of broth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium and simmer for 10 minutes partially covered. Cool slightly.
Puree the soup along with the cooked beets in a blender or a food processor until smooth.
Return to the pot. Season with salt and pepper.
Add some of remaining broth for thinner soup, if desired.
Garnish with sour cream and chives.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Place vinegar, salt and pepper in salad bowl.
Mix well to dissolve salt.
Add olive oil and mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, corn syrup and salt and mix well.
Stir in oleo, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Is done when knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese, milk and salt.
Mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add additional mayonnaise just before serving if desired.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: onion casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with generous layer of potato chips.
Cover potato chips with thin sliced onions. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix 1 can soup with 1 can water and pour over all.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook about 20 minutes longer.

title: family reunion cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan. While still warm, poke holes in the cake using toothpicks.
Pour pineapple and juice over cake.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and milk (will be thick).
Spread over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip. Cover and chill before serving.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In pie plate arrange tortilla chips in a single layer.
Spoon a little salsa over each chip.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put in oven to melt cheese 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Makes 20 servings.

title: "mr." barry's favorite millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with milk and very small amount of paraffin wax over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add pecans, drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Melt Hershey bars with small amount of paraffin wax and dip caramels (using toothpick) into chocolate; put on wax paper.
Go at a fast pace so chocolate won't harden.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and bring to a boil first 3 ingredients.
Place dill and cloves in a heat-proof container.
Quarter cukes lengthwise and fill container.
Pour hot liquid over cukes and let stand for approximately 12 hours at room temperature and then refrigerate.

title: cream cheese tuna dip
directions: Stir milk, one tablespoon at a time, into cream cheese.
Mix in salad dressing, onions, horseradish, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in tuna. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch glass casserole along with cooked spaghetti.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread the canned pie filling over the pineapple.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the pie filling.
Cut the margarine in chunks and place on cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; follow directions on taco mix package.
Serve ingredients in separate bowls.
Let everyone assemble individual salads or layer in a large bowl as follows: lettuce, chips, meat, cheese, tomatoes, onions, salsa and sour cream.

title: custard coconut pie
directions: Blend all, except coconut, in blender for 5 minutes.
Stir in coconut.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch pie dish.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: katherine's strawberry cookies
directions: In saucepan, heat butter; add eggs and sugar.
Mix well, stirring constantly.
Blend in dates; reduce heat to low.
Add flour, stirring and cooking until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Cool for 2 hours.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a pan and cook until it comes to a full boil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let set.

title: caldo
directions: You will need a stewpot.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes. Take off of heat. Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well. Pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: freezer strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Stem and thoroughly crush about 1 pint strawberries and measure 1 cup into large bowl.
Grind very fine (do not peel) about 1 pound rhubarb.
Measure 1 cup and add to berries.
Thoroughly mix sugar into fruit; let sit 10 minutes.
Mix water and pectin in small saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir into fruit and stir about 3 minutes.
Ladle quickly into containers.
Cover at once with tight lids.
Let stand at room temperature until set (may take up to 24 hours).
Store in freezer. Makes 5 cups.

title: mississippi fried chicken with brown gravy
directions: Heat oil gently and stir in flour. Stir continually and cook for several minutes. It should not be allowed to get lumpy. Add hot liquid slowly, still stirring, until desired consistency is reached. Other seasoning may be added.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Tastes like pecan pie!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Select
firm, smooth sweet potatoes.
Bake uncovered in 425° oven
until soft;
cool, peel and slice in half and place in buttered
pan
or
baking
dish.
Sprinkle generously with white sugar, then drizzle generously with white Karo.
Sprinkle lightly with
lemon juice.
Dot with butter or margarine. Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, eggs (slightly beaten), shredded cheese and salt.
Place all ingredients, except corn flakes, in a 2-quart Pyrex casserole.
Crush corn flakes and place on top.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lettuce and cauliflower salad
directions: Place lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon into a large bowl. Mix salad dressing, cheese and sugar.
Mix thoroughly with lettuce mixture about 1 hour before serving.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together in a container with lid (to store as well). Serve by using 2 to 3 heaping spoonfuls (to taste) and hot water.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk; mix. Place desired amount of dough on floured cloth.
Pat out.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Let warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Place remaining dough in fridge for future use.
Will keep 8 to 10 days.

title: spinach dip
directions: After spinach has drained, squeeze any remaining moisture out with hands.
Mix with other ingredients and chill overnight.
Best when served with Hawaiian bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Drain canned fruit.
Add fruit to Cool Whip and stir.
Add coconut and stir.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Chill and serve.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients except ham and cheese.
Spread mixture on a 10 x 12-inch sheet of wax paper.
Arrange ham on top, leaving a small space around edge.
Place cheese on top of ham.
Starting from short end, roll up jelly-roll style.
Seal ends and edges. Place seam side down in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Place rest of cheese on top; cut in triangles.
Return to oven about 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: chocolate ice cream sauce
directions: Boil and stir constantly until thick; takes about 15 minutes. Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lemon lush
directions: For crust, mix the butter, flour and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apple bake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add all remaining ingredients and bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: googalie
directions: Cook pasta, sausage links and ground sausage (ground sausage should be cooked as if browning hamburger).
Drain tomatoes and cut up into edible chunks.
Grind or dice cheese.
Layer ingredients into casserole dish in following order:
pasta, cheese, tomatoes and ground sausage.
Layer until dish is full. Top with sausage links and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: rhubarb slush
directions: Boil rhubarb, lemon juice and sugar until mushy. Strain if desired. Add jello and vodka. Freeze. To serve fill glass with slush and add 7up.

title: coffee-scotch dessert
directions: Prepare pudding mix following package directions.
Pour into 4 dessert dishes.
Chill for short time, if desired.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large Ziploc bag. One at a time, dip chicken breast in buttermilk, then place in bag and shake to coat. Place in pan coated with nonstick spray. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into large bowl.	Beat until well-mashed. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend,
then beat at medium speed of electric
mixer,
for
2 minutes.
Pour into a well greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.	Bake at 350° for 60 or 70 minutes.
Cool
in	pan
at
least 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Finish
cooling
on
rack.	Sprinkle with
confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: cranberry salad deluxe(serves 12)
directions: Add sugar to fruits and then add Cool Whip and marshmallows. Blend together and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in a stockpot.
Pour in onions; cook until soft. Add pumpkin and broth.
Cook for 30 minutes at a slow simmer. Remove mixture and blend in food processor.
Put back in pot.
Add hot sauce and nutmeg to taste along with pepper.
Cook 15 minutes. Add cream and bring just to a boil.
Serve immediately with chopped chives on top.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Toss together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake for 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: slot key copycat rolls
directions: You will need 5 (5-inch) soups bowls or 5 (1 1/2 pound) Dinty Moore stew cans.

title: chicken tortellini alfredo
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package, adding broccoli to water during last 3 minutes of pasta cooking time; drain.

title: rigatoni pasta salad
directions: Cook rigatoni according to box instructions; drain with cool water.
Chop peppers, black olives and green onions into pieces. Mix macaroni and vegetables in large bowl.
Pour Italian dressing over mixture.
Sprinkle with salad seasoning.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add tomato right before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cheese, then crumbled sausage or ham.
Beat eggs; add milk and spices.
Pour over ingredients in pan and sprinkle rest of cheese over.
Drizzle melted butter over all. Refrigerate overnight.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until eggs are set.
Serves 6 (x 4 for "Firehouse serving).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, then mix in shrimp and cocktail sauce. Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix
in
a
large
bowl.
Beat eggs, then add the other ingredients, one at a time, beating well after each ingredient is added.
Bake
at
325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in a tube pan that has been well-greased and floured.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook together until hard ball stage (stringy).
Pour over pecans. Stir until all are coated.

title: patricia's orzo fruit salad
directions: Beat Eggs, add Sugar, Flour and drained Juices.
Place in pan and cook until thick like pudding.
Cook Orzo during this time according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine Orzo and fruit juice pudding mixture; stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add Fruit, Cook Whip and Nuts the next day.

title: jello coconut pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Set aside 1/4 cup coconut and cover.
Stir remaining coconut into batter.

title: beef with peppers
directions: Place mushrooms in medium bowl; add enough warm water to cover mushrooms completely.
Let stand 30 minutes; drain.
Squeeze excess water from mushrooms.
Remove and discard stems.
Slice caps into thin strips.
Combine cornstarch, bouillon granules, additional 1/4 cup water, soy sauce and sesame oil in small bowl; mix well.
Set aside.

title: chili and corn bread
directions: Brown beef in large skillet and drain.
Add seasoning mix, corn, beans, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare cornbread mix with egg and milk. Pour over chili mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cornbread is browned.

title: baked turkey chile rellenos
directions: Lightly coat an 11 x 7 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange chilies in dish and top half of each with Jack cheese and turkey (cut as necessary to fit chilies).
Fold edges of chilies together and place seam side down in dish.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
