In another bowl, whisk together the milk and eggs.
Add this to the flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Pour over the chilies.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn off the heat.
Sprinkle the cheddar cheese over the top and return to the oven 1 minute to melt the cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Combine remaining cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg. Press into pan.

title: pecan puff
directions: Beat egg white.
Add light brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans until well coated.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: saucy beef strips
directions: Cut steak in thin strips; brown in butter.
Stir in water, jelly, lemon juice and gravy mix.
Heat to boiling; sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Simmer pineapple and sugar.
Bake cake at 350°, punch holes then cover with pineapple.
Mix pudding as directed.
Add coconut, then spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: old-fashioned peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into ice cream churn.
Pour ice around inside of churn.
Cover with rock salt.

title: easy creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat soup and milk just until well blended.
Arrange potatoes, onions and soup in layers in buttered casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: michelle's 3 bean chili
directions: Brown meat, then add onion.
Add beans and seasonings; cook for 30 minutes.
Serve hot, along with cornbread or crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions in skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off any grease.
Spoon beef into 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth. Pour mixture over casserole covering evenly.
Set oven at 400° and bake for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
I serve a tossed salad with this casserole.

title: suzanne's oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugars and oleo.
Stir until oleo is melted.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Mix well.
Add 6 ounces chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add milk and sugar; mix well.
Boil for 3 minutes; remove from burner.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Cool approximately 1 hour before cutting.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Add onions, celery and shrimp.
Add mayonnaise and dressing to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and next 5 ingredients (set aside). Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 3 minutes in a heavy saucepan on medium heat.
Be careful not to burn.
Drop on wax paper and knead in food coloring to desired color.
Can be divided into several pieces before coloring to make several colors.
This is great to keep at home for small children!

title: carrots and pineapple(serves 2 to any number)
directions: Cook the carrots in a minimum amount of water (I usually cover the bottom of the pot to about 3/4 inch and put the carrots in a steamer).
Pour off the juice from pineapple and add cornstarch. Mix together the carrots and pineapple and add brown sugar.
Cook until tender.
Add pineapple juice and cornstarch.
The juice becomes thickened and glossy.
Add a small amount of lemon juice (1 to 2 teaspoons).
Serve with beef, ham, chicken or fish.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce, nuts and pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: valentine cookies
directions: In
bowl
cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Gradually add dry ingredients and molasses;
mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
On
lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Using
3-inch cookie cutter (heart shaped), cut out cookies.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in oil until meat turns white.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook until slightly browned.
Add tomatoes, corn, salt and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine with meat mixture.
Stir in grated cheese.
Bake in 2 two-quart baking dishes, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 9.

title: dump cake
directions: Gently layer ingredients in order listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not stir or mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Very good over ice cream.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in pear juice and bring to a boil.
Cool. Mix cream cheese and add Jell-O mixture to that.

title: slime cake
directions: Make the cake according to box.
You need to make two 8 or 9-inch layers.
Make vanilla pudding according to box.
Put in 8 to o12 drops green food coloring.
Blend ingredients.
Cover mixture and chill for at least 1 hour or until you are ready to use it.

title: granny's chicken salad
directions: Cut up and boil chicken until done.
Cool and remove meat from bones.
Chop or cube chicken finely.

title: corn and sausage chowder
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and brown; drain off fat.
Put sausage into a deep pan.
Return 2 tablespoons of fat to the pan and saute the onion with the sausage.
Add the potatoes, salt, pepper, basil and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in creamed corn, corn and liquid and evaporated milk.
Cover and heat almost to boiling.
Serve with French bread and a salad.

title: fried spaghetti with shrimp
directions: Fry onion in oil but do not brown.
Cool.
Add string beans and tomatoes to pan and fry all.
Dip shrimp in egg and place in original pan.
Stir-fry until golden brown.
Set aside.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet relishgroves, texas
directions: Chop tomatoes, bell peppers, cabbage and onions in food processor.

title: potato salad
directions: Leaving skin on potatoes, cook in a pressure cooker for 20 minutes or until soft.
Insert knife into center of potatoes to check if done.
Cool potatoes.
Remove skin and cube.
Hard-boil the eggs and cool them.
Chop eggs and add to potatoes along with onion.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Start with 1/2 a jar and add more if desired.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: honey bear punch
directions: Freeze cherries in ring.
Pineapple and grapefruit juice cans should be equal.
Mix honey, pineapple and grapefruit juices.
Add gin or vodka.
Add ginger ale and top with sliced fruit and cherries frozen in ring.
Enjoy.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Boil sugar and water for 2 minutes.
Add salt and cornstarch, dissolved in a little cold water.
Boil and stir until clear and smooth.
Melt chocolate in a little hot water; add to syrup.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Serve hot.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw Rhodes bread dough and let rise per instructions.
Roll out dough and rub with oleo.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano, garlic powder and slightly with oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Cover with pepperoni slices.
Spread grated Mozzarella cheese over top.
Roll up and pinch ends shut.
Lay on greased cookie sheet and brush with an egg.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant with onion in a small amount of salted water until done, and drain.
Beat 1 egg and add to milk, pour over toast cubes and allow to set a few minutes. To eggplant add cheese, butter, black and red pepper.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wake up breakfast
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 1 minute. Drink immediately.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet.
In heavy 3-quart saucepan, stir together corn syrup, sugar, water and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until temperature reaches 280° on candy thermometer or until small amount dropped into very cold water separates into threads which are hard, but not brittle.
Gradually stir in peanuts; continue cooking, stirring frequently until temperature reaches 300°.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda.
Immediately pour mixture onto baking sheet. Spread mixture evenly to edges of sheet.
Cool.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in bottom of pan.
Knead the flour, Crisco, milk, salt and baking powder after mixing together.
Roll out dough and spread out peach pie filling on dough.
Take and roll dough into a jelly roll, then cut slices and lay in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix water, sugar, vanilla flavoring and lemon juice.
Pour over the slices and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: good chicken
directions: Drain off some of broth and add chicken soup, English peas, pimentos and butter.
Also add onion and bell pepper and put in casserole dish with grated cheese on top.
Cook in medium oven until bubbly.

title: pat's clam chowder
directions: Do not drain clams.

title: frosted salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water, and 7-UP well. Chill until partially set. Add crushed pineapple (well drained). Add marshmallows and sliced bananas.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake the layer. Take one layer and crumble it in bowl. Put in first box of strawberries over this. Cake mix, cream cheese and sugar put in separate bowl makes an icing over the layers. Make up your first box of vanilla pudding and pour over icing. Top it with first bowl of Cool Whip. Then repeat again. Let set for 24 hours.

title: buttermilk donuts
directions: Mix together, roll out, cut and deep fry.

title: "the best" barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels with water over low heat. Stir in chopped pecans. Spray pan and spoon out into individual pieces and let cool. Melt chocolate chips and cooking wax over water.
Dip caramel pieces into chocolate and set.

title: cheese baked fish
directions: Cut fish into 4 or 5 pieces.
Add butter to shallow baking dish.
Place in 375° oven to melt.
Mix crumbs, cheese and salt. Spread mayonnaise on one side of fish and roll in crumb mixture. Repeat on the other side.
Remove the baking dish from oven and arrange fish in single layer.
Turn fish to coat with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, pecans, onion and Tabasco sauce, mixing well.
Mold into a ring and chill.

title: thrifty meat and corn casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well.
Bake at 350°
for	1
hour. When done, it will be loose, so serve with spoon.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat (drain), onion and green pepper; add seasonings, sugar, tomatoes and water.
Place in large baking dish; stir in rice and bake at 350° until rice is tender.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Finely chop carrot and onion.
Place in mixing bowl and add all remaining ingredients except mushrooms.
Combine, being careful not to overmix.
Turn half of the meat mixture into a greased 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Make a slight indentation in center of meat and place mushrooms in well, reserving a few for garnish.
Cover with remaining meat and pat gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
After baking, garnish with remaining mushrooms sauteed in butter.
Serves 6.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then pour water, vinegar, vanilla and oil over flour mixture. Mix all together well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Then cool.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk as directed on package.
Add the remaining 1 3/4 cup milk and the pudding mix.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell and garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator at least 4 hours.

title: southern spareribs
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic salt on ribs.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over ribs and bake until tender.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef, sausage, eggs, salt and pepper.
Combine bread crumbs and milk; add meat to mixture.
Form into small meat balls.
Brown in a small amount of oil in skillet.
After meat balls are brown, remove from pan and saute onion in same pan.
Stir in flour; add meat stock, put meat balls back into mixture and simmer 1 hour. When ready to serve, stir in sour cream.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add egg, milk, ham and seasoning.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet milk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Mix in the oil or cut in the shortening.
Add the milk and mix well.
The dough should be easy to handle.
Turn out onto a floured surface, flour your hands and gently knead dough to form a smooth ball.
Flatten the dough with your hands and roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Mix together the pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells in 3-quarts boiling water for 18 minutes or until tender but slightly firm.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water, then drain well.

title: apple betty
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt the margarine.
Add crumbs and saute until crisp and deep golden.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; stir in peel.
Sprinkle a third of crumbs evenly in greased 2 1/2 -quart casserole or souffle dish.
Arrange half of apples over top.
Sprinkle with a third of sugar mixture.
Top with a third more of crumbs, remaining apples, a third more of sugar mix, remaining crumbs and remaining sugar mix.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° about 50 minutes or until topping is well browned and apples are tender.
Cool on rack about 20 minutes. Spoon out while hot or very warm.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired. Can be frozen, is also good plain.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dilute lemonade by half.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: charlotte's soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add other ingredients; let simmer.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix with mixer until well blended.
Spread on a platter or large pan.
Layer rest of ingredients over sauce.
Dip with taco chips or Fritos.

title: tuna stuffed eggs
directions: Remove shells from eggs; cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mix all ingredients, except egg whites.
Fill egg whites with mixture.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Place in baking dish.
After mixing and bringing to a boil, pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° to 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chip dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a double boiler, stirring until melted.

title: chicken fried potatoes
directions: Place all the dry ingredients in a plastic or paper bag and mix well.
Add potatoes that have been peeled and quartered.
Melt oleo in large pan.
Add potatoes to melted oleo.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
When they have baked for 25 minutes, turn potatoes over in the pan so they will brown evenly.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes and onion in layers in a greased 3-quart baking dish, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Trim fat from pork chops and save it for later.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Brown chops on both sides.
When brown set aside for a minute.
Mix the remaining flour with the drippings in the pan.
Add milk and blend lightly until smooth. Cook to the consistency of a thin white sauce.
Pour sauce over potatoes and chops in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all.
Make into small balls.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Blend in sandwich spread, salt and pepper to taste.
Refill whites with mixture.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chewy bars
directions: Blend all ingredients well in medium bowl.
Spread batter in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut as desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake one hour at 350°.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O together.
Stir in mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: chiffon nut cake
directions: In large bowl with wooden spoon, mix sugar, oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla.

title: ida's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown until onions are done.
Add hamburger.
Cook well done; then add stewed tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 1 hour over low heat.
Serves 8.

title: pralines a-la-microwave
directions: Combine sugar, milk and salt in a deep 3-quart microwavable bowl.
Mix well. Stir in butter.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 1/2 minutes (soft ball), stirring once.
Stir in pecans. Cool 1 minute.
Beat by hand until creamy and thicker.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Brown cubes in butter until crisp.
Combine pineapple, eggs, flour and sugar.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered baking dish and put browned crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until thick, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Cream oleo with white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add oats.
Mix well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in oven at 325°.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Whip egg white and water until frothy.
Stir pecans into egg mixture until coated.
Mix sugar and spices together and stir into nuts until completely covered.
Turn out on greased cookie sheet and spread evenly, separating nuts.
Bake in slow oven (200°) for 45 minutes.
Cool and wrap for gifts or eat "em" up!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 375° for one hour.
Bake in two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and Crisco; beat until blended.
Add vanilla.
Add flour; 1 cup at a time.
To help mix, add heavy cream.
Grease Bundt cake pan.
Add mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Remove from cake pan after cool, then enjoy.

title: date pudding
directions: Put nuts, dates, sugar, baking powder and flour into a bowl; pour milk over bread cubes.
Add beaten eggs.
Pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a souffle dish.
Put teapot of water on to boil.
Beat margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well each time.
Mix in flour, mix in milk (1/2 at a time).
Mix in juice and rind.
Beat whites until stiff peaks and fold into batter.
Carefully pour into dish. Set dish into another pan and pour boiling water halfway up. Bake for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: 30-day friendship cake
directions: Mix together in gallon
jar.
Stir well.
Stir everyday with a wooden spoon.
Keep top on loosely.

title: chocolate kiss thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Set aside.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, sugar, milk, vanilla and egg yolk.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add melted chocolate.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, cornmeal, vinegar, vanilla, milk and melted butter. Pour into unbaked 9 inch pie shell. Bake at 350°F for 35-40 minutes. Pie will
be golden brown when done.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop together celery, onion, pimento and green pepper.
Boil a minute, sugar, water, celery seed, salad oil and vinegar.
Pour mixture over sauerkraut that has been rinsed and drained.
Let stand 24 hours or at least overnight.
This will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: bean and dumplings
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients as for soup.
Mix together dry ingredients with water or milk.
Roll dough thin and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop into boiling bean soup.
Lower heat and cook 15 minutes or until dumplings are cooked.

title: thank you mother, one dish cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put first 4 ingredients into ovenproof dish, mix with spoon until just blended.
Add fruit, stir gently.

title: pigs in the blanket(hamburger)
directions: Place cabbage in pot; pour boiling water over cabbage and cook 10 minutes, boiling.
Turn cabbage to cook 5 additional minutes. Don't overcook.
Remove leaves.
Mix ground beef, rice, eggs, chopped onion and 1/2 cup of tomato sauce with salt and pepper to season.
Put 2 teaspoons of mixture on leaf.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place rack in bottom of a large pot; spread extra leaves on rack.
Fill 3/4 full of tomatoes and put in pigs. Cook on high until boiling, then medium for 1 hour and low for remaining time.
Total cooking time is 2 1/2 hours.
Makes about 15 Pigs In The Blanket.

title: broiled soft shell crabs
directions: Clean crabs; drop them in oil.
Salt and pepper.
Have broiler hot (500°).
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve on toast with melted butter, parsley and sliced onions.

title: bread and butter pickles(no canning)
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Put into a jar.
Slice cucumbers and onions and put in jar.
Eat as desired.
Just keep adding cucumbers.

title: hot ham and cheese rounds
directions: Slice off top third of loaf; hollow out bottom section, leaving a 1/2-inch shell.
Combine mayonnaise, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Brush inside of bread with 1/4 cup mayonnaise mixture, reserving remainder.

title: julia's quick potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes, cook until done and cool.
Drain relish and pimentos.
Then mix all ingredients well.
Yields 5 servings.
Can be adjusted for a crowd.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash and onions with salt and leave in refrigerator for 1 hour. Mix and bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, celery seeds and bell peppers. Add squash mixture and put into pint jars and seal.

title: brazilian burnt eggs
directions: In a pan, combine the water, sugar and cinnamon stick.
Bring to boil, uncovered, over medium-high heat.
Boil until thickened (like syrup).
To this syrup, add the eggs, stirring always, until the syrup dries up and the eggs burn a little.
Then pour the milk, slowly to moisten it.
When well blended, add butter.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle some powdered cinnamon over.

title: grandma chamberlin's boston brown bread
directions: Boil 2 cups of water; pour over dates.
Set aside to cool. In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add date mixture, nuts, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into 5 well-greased cans (16 ounce vet cans), filling half full. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from cans while still warm.
Cool completely.
Slice thin.
Spread with butter or cream cheese.

title: best hot chocolate
directions: Add as many miniature marshmallows to the mixture as you want. Mix all together and put in an airtight container.
When ready to use, put 2 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.

title: seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese 1 to 2 minutes with electric mixer until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except almonds; sprinkle with paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine macaroni, cheese, tuna, pickles and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over macaroni and toss.
Yummy!

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Prepare first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Drain well.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, mushroom soup and margarine in saucepan; heat until butter is melted.
Add sliced almonds.
Pour into casserole and top with onions rings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour in hot oil.
Cook to a golden brown, 2 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: jello-ice cream pudding
directions: Mix jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add ice cream; stir until dissolved.
Place in fridge until firm.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with topping and bake for 45 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: luscious lemon chicken
directions: In a
skillet,	brown
chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat. Add
remaining
ingredients, except lemon slices.
Cook, covered, over
low
heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Put seasoned stuffing mix in plastic bag.
Add salt.
Beat egg with water in pie plate.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture, then shake in stuffing mixture.
Place in melted butter in single layer. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Simmer 40 minutes and serve on buns.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add chili and peppers. Stir.
Add cheese and simmer until melted.
(Best to cut cheese in small pieces.)

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard hot pepper.
Quickly spoon hot relish into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yield:
10 half pints.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, beef, green onions and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into serving bowls.
Serve with crackers.

title: homemade mints
directions: Blend cream cheese, oil and food coloring in bowl.
Add confectioners sugar; knead until well mixed.
Shape into marble sized balls.
Leave ball-shaped or press into patty, if desired. Roll in sugar.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put spinach in greased casserole dish. Combine rest of ingredients and pour over spinach.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot mock lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions until tender. Drain ground beef and sausage; drain.
Place in lightly greased crock-pot and add all remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix thoroughly.
Cover.
Cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
Can cook on high for 3 to 5 hours.

title: fiesta cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg. Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.

title: caribbean banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch broilerproof pan; set aside.

title: cheese torte
directions: Pour cold water into bowl, sprinkle with gelatin.
Heat egg yolks slightly; add sugar, salt and milk.
Cook over boiling water until it reaches a custard consistency.
Stir until dissolved. Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cheese and vanilla. Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat egg whites separately until stiff.
Fold whipped cream and egg whites into beaten mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, real good with a whisk and cook at medium temperature (burner) on stove, stirring all the time with the whisk until filling thickens, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into the pie shell and top with meringue.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Heat the oven 400°.
Unroll crescent roll dough and fit into a 12 inch pizza pan, pressing seams together to form a crust. Sprinkle with the defrosted hash browns and cheese.
Beat the egg in a bowl and season with salt and pepper.
Pour over the pizza. Place Canadian bacon cubes on top.
Bake 20 minutes, until eggs are set and crust is golden.

title: vegetable soup 2
directions: Mix and simmer for 1 hour. Cool-freeze.

title: jello mousse
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
When dissolved add yogurt right away and hand mix together.
Refrigerate until set. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine
cake
mix, walnuts and coconut in bowl, mixing well. Layer
pie
filling,
then
pineapple
and then coconut mixture in a
x
9-inch
baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown, 10 to 12 servings.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Combine cut-up lettuce, onion and salt in a bowl.
Cut bacon into small pieces, fry until crisp; do not drain.
Remove from heat and add vinegar, then sugar and mix well.
Return to heat and slowly add beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Stir on heat until mixture thickens.
Pour over lettuce while warm.
Mix and serve while still warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion-olive bread
directions: Slice onions and place in frying pan with sugar, salt and pepper.
Do not add any liquid to pan.
Saute until onions are transparent but still crunchy.
Make sure all water has evaporated; if not, drain.
Roll out pizza dough in large rectangle.
Spread onions and olives over dough.
Sprinkle with red pepper and olive oil.
Cover with Mozzarella.
Fold sides in and roll jelly roll style.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until browned.

title: tuna broccoli pie
directions: *May substitute crescent rolls or package of refrigerator rolls, but pie crust is best.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together soup, cheese, milk, mayo and egg, then pour over broccoli.
Mix together bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix everything.
Spary with Pam.
Make a cute fat cookie. Bake. Wash hands.
Hand fan pan.
Eat hot cookie with cold milk. Yummy!

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Scald 1 3/4 cups milk with Karo in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Blend cornstarch and remaining 1/4 cup milk in small bowl.
Mix in sugar and salt.
Add egg yolks and beat until well blended.
Add quickly, all at once, to scalded milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie crust. Cover with meringue and bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: banana cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla, mashed banana and sour milk to mixture.
In separate bowl, sift the cake flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Pour flour mixture into the butter sugar mixture gradually, stirring
until ingredients are evenly blended.
Flour and grease 2 round cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool.
Use basic white icing for frosting.
Place sliced banana between layers.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Filling:
Cook raisins in water for about 1 hour until tender. Sweeten to taste, add 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Line bowl with lemon and orange slices.
Chop high-quality beef such as top round into 1-inch chunks and add to bowl.
Pour marinade over.
Refrigerate, uncovered, for at least 1 day.
(Can last up to 1 week.)

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender except lettuce and croutons. Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: corned beef rolls
directions: Mix together and spread both sides of Pepperidge Farm tea rolls.
Add small piece of thin sliced kosher or gourmet-style corned beef and Swiss cheese on.
Wrap in Reynolds Wrap and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: ommy's russian salad dressing
directions: Mix all together, except the oil.
Add oil slowly and beat thoroughly.
Makes 1 cup of dressing.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms; wash and dice.
Saute in olive oil until tender.
Add bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and crushed garlic, stirring constantly until crumbs are toasted.
Spoon over mushrooms and spoon on melted margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk to pudding; stir (do not whip).
Put bananas and cookies in layers in another dish.
Pour other ingredients over vanilla wafers and bananas.
Use other half of Cool Whip for topping and chill.

title: pickled meat
directions: Cook slowly until brine will carry an egg.
Cool the brine.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Hand mix flour, sugar and salt.
Boil in pan the oleo, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Pour boiling mixture over flour mixture and stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla and mix.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease loaf pan. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs and beat until fluffy.

Blend in dry ingredients alternately with mangos. Mix until smooth. Add nuts and raisins. Pour into loaf pan. Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: oriental wings
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir until chicken is coated with sauce.
Bake for 15 minutes, then stir again.
Bake for 20 minutes more, until tender. Makes great appetizers.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Pour boiling water over mixture and blend well.
Pour into well-greased oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, soda and salt.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time (up to 1 1/2 cups, you can use your mixer, then you have to stir by hand).
Stir into mixture the chips.
The dough should be stiff enough that when pressed with a clean finger, no dough sticks.
Place by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 9 minutes. Cookies should be just lightly brown on top and edges.

title: power pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in sealed container 2 hours before serving.

title: italian sausage quiche
directions: Combine sausage with other ingredients.
Pour mixture into deep dish 9-inch pie shell or individual petite shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and add bell pepper, onion and pimientos. Add mayonnaise to suit taste.
Stir in bacon.
Can be refrigerated for 3 days.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jellied cranberry sauce and 1 cup hot water in blender. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup water and add to cranberry mixture.
Pour 1/2 mixture in an 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Spread sour cream over top of chilled mixture.
Add second half of Jell-O mix over sour cream.
Sprinkle nuts on top (optional). Refrigerate.

title: plantation supper
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in milk, soup and cheese until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Corn should be drained.

title: lily salad
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup milk.
Cook over low heat, just until liquid coats a spoon.
Let cool in mixing bowl.
Mix the fruit and marshmallows (cut in small pieces or use small marshmallows).
Add this to egg mixture.
Whip the cream and add 2 tablespoons sugar; fold into mixture of fruit.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil and vinegar or lemon juice.
Add mustard, celery salt and mayonnaise; mix well and pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pepper steak(serves 6)
directions: Cut steak into small cubes.
Brown in shortening about 10 minutes, or until tender.
Add soy sauce and water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add onion and bell pepper, which have been cut into strips.
Cook until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: mince
directions: In large frypan, cook onions in butter and add crumbled ground beef; brown.
Cover with water.
To this, add sliced carrots and simmer until tender.
When done, make gravy with juices in pan. Thicken and serve over mashed potatoes.

title: green sweet relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions, peppers and cucumbers with fine blade of chopper.
Mix together with salt; let stand overnight.

title: super cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over pudding mixture. Top with whipped topping. Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: jello dessert (or green goop)
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and jello.
Mix together.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Chill well.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs (1 at a time) and then add Hershey's syrup and mix well.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Bake in long pan at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter.
Stir in popcorn, peanuts, M&M's and candy corn.
Mix well.
Press into buttered tube pan.
Put in refrigerator.
Remove and cut into slices.
Stays together better if kept in refrigerator.

title: black skillet beef with greens and red potatoes
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across the grain into long strips 1/8-inch thick.
Thoroughly coat strips with hot 'n spicy seasoning.
Spray a large heavy skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat pan over high heat.
Add meat; cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, onions, broth and garlic.
Cook covered over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Stir in carrots.
Lay greens over top and cook covered until carrots are tender, about 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
Calories 342, total fat 4 grams.

title: pecan float
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Crumble cookies into the pudding mixture. Stir in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs on top. Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread, torn into pieces, into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together eggs, milk, sugar, margarine, raisins and pecans.
Pour over bread slices.
Bake at 375° until edges puff and turn brown.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook
sugar
and buttermilk on high heat for 6 minutes; add soda.
Stir
on
lower flame until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir often and cool slightly.
Add chopped pecans and vanilla.
Beat and drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub and coat 4 potatoes with oil.
Wrap in foil.
Bake. Halve lengthwise.
Scoop out insides.
Salt and pepper shells. Peel two boiled potatoes and mash with insides of baked potatoes. Beat in all ingredients, except grated cheese.
Fill shells with mixture; top with grated cheese.
Return to oven and bake until hot.
Yields 8 servings.
May be frozen for later use.
I freeze in Ziploc bags and take out only what I need for a meal.

title: chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms and pepper before baking.
Cover; bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Pour into a big bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Makes a large amount.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in an 8 x 8-inch (or 2-quart) glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except butter, in medium mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Microwave for 12 to 16 minutes on High or until apples are tender. Do not cover.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: quick peach pie or apple pie
directions: Place sliced peaches in a pie plate and sprinkle a little sugar over them to keep them from turning brown.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 or 5 fingers and weave into a lattice crust on top of peaches.
Mix sugar, flour, melted butter and egg well; coat crust with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab casserole ala e. hoffman
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter on top of double boiler.
Combine all ingredients (do not precook noodles).
Mix well and place in baking dish.
Add sherry, sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly at 375°.
May sprinkle with a little paprika.

title: flintstone bread dip
directions: Cut top off Flintstone bread.
Pull out center of bread in pieces and arrange around outside of bread on a plate.
Combine other ingredients and fill bread with mixture.
Dip bread chunks and enjoy.

title: pot roast for two
directions: On top of stove, place patties, carrots, potatoes and onions in pan.
Cover with water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add chopped cabbage on top and cook 10 minutes more.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Add sugar to melted butter; beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: hot beef cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on a glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers. Spread or dip crackers.

title: pecan coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare dough and bake bottom crust for 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Melt margarine in large
pot, then add flour and mix well. Add milk, broth,
salt
and
pepper.
Stir	over medium heat until thickened.	Add more flour if needed.
Turn heat to low and add chicken and
vegetables.
Stir to combine and pour into pie shell. Cover with
rolled dough.	Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in three layers or sheet cake pan at 300° or 350° until done.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Blend sugar
and
oil; add eggs and beat well.	Add all dry ingredients;
blend
thoroughly.
Add
sweet potatoes and vanilla and
mix
well;
bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 350°.
Can also be put in baking pan (optional).
Cream cheese icing is good on cake also.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, then mix well after each egg.
Add salt and baking powder to flour.
Mix well, then add flour mix and sour cream alternately.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix bread crumbs with milk until milk has been absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients, except chili sauce.
Place in an ungreased loaf pan.
Cover top with chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: buttermilk chicken dinner
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine water, bouillon, thyme, rosemary and bay leaves.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place chicken, breast side down, in casserole.
Microwave, covered, on High 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Arrange potatoes, onions and carrots around chicken.

Cook, covered, on Medium 30 to 40 minutes or until drumsticks move easily in the sockets and vegetables are tender, giving dish a half turn and rearranging vegetables once. Transfer chicken and vegetables to platter.
Keep warm.

title: mamaw's buttermilk salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O by directions on package.
Mix pineapple into Jell-O.
Let cool.
Mix buttermilk, fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: beef stroganoff sandwich
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Cut bread in half lengthwise. Butter both halves.
Place on baking sheets.
Stir sour cream in meat mixture.
Spoon onto bread.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, green pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: four cheese pasta sauce
directions: In saucepan, whisk or stir milk and sauce mix until blended. Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce for 8 ounces pasta, cooked and drained.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese and freshly ground pepper.
With pasta, makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended with cheese.
Shape into balls, then roll in chopped pecans and shape.

title: french-fried onion rings
directions: Peel onion.
Cut into slices and separate into rings.
Heat oil to 375°.
Beat dry ingredients into milk.
Dip each ring into batter.
Fry until golden brown.

title: hunting camp cobbler
directions: Combine peaches with 1 cup sugar and simmer for 5 minutes. Melt butter in 1-quart glass baking dish.

title: waffles
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In a medium bowl mix egg yolks and melted oleo.
Add this mixture in a large bowl; then beat egg whites and fold into the batter.
Add milk; don't beat.
Mixture will be kind of lumpy.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart jar and shake well. Refrigerate.
Makes one quart.

title: aunt ellie's green salad(put into layers in sheet cake type dish)
directions: Note:
I use a lot of Parmesan cheese, enough to make a layer.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onions in bacon grease.
Mix other ingredients and add to beans.
Add sauteed onion.
Crumble bacon and add to beans. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: In a medium size bowl beat the yolks until smooth and lemony. Gradually add honey, beating until well blended and thick.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Stir beaten eggs into the yolk and honey mixture.
In a heavy bottom saucepan, combine cream and egg mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until the mixture thickens, about 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in sugar and vanilla while mixture is hot.
Chill thoroughly before attempting to freeze.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Melt butter in medium-sized saucepan over moderate heat.
Remove; beat in sugars, egg and vanilla with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in flour mixtures, apple and walnuts until combined.
Spread into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until top springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 16 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until soft.
Drain and cool.
Blend hard-boiled egg yolks with mustard.
Cut egg whites into salad.
Combine all ingredients.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Combine chocolate, 1 cup marshmallows, water and butter in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted.
Cool slightly.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and thick enough to spread (about 2 minutes).
Stir in remaining 1 cup marshmallows and nuts.
Frosts top of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: grandpa's teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Use to marinate 2 to 3 pounds of meat.
Cook as directed.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add one cup buttermilk.
Put in refrigerator until begins to jell.
Take out and add 1 3/4 cups Cool Whip and stir well.
Put in your favorite dish.

title: stephanie's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Mix crushed crackers and melted butter.
Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes and lay on top of broccoli in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until about 1/2 done, drain well.
Combine with green pepper and onion.
Mix together tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, rosemary, vinegar, oil, sugar, dry mustard and basil.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate 12 hours before serving.
May be served hot or cold.
Keeps well.

title: student veggie burger
directions: Drain juice from beans and crush in mixing bowl.
When beans are mashed into a paste, add sauce, diced green pepper and diced onion.
Add bread crumbs or crushed crackers until mixture can be formed into patties.
Heat 1/8 cup oil in pan; grill patties. Sandwich patty with desired toppings and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine ham, onion, soup, cream, salt and pepper.
Thinly slice potatoes and fold into ham mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Remove foil and grate croutons over potatoes and return to oven and bake uncovered for 15-20 minutes more.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour blueberry pie filling in baking dish.
Pour cake mix over filling.
Then pour melted butter over mix.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: texas burritos
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, seasonings, flour, tomatoes and chilies. Cook until beef is almost done.
Heat tortillas in dry skillet on both sides.
Spread with heated refried beans.
Spread ground beef mixture over beans. Roll up.
Place seam side down in shallow baking dish. Cover with foil.
Keep warm in oven.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add flour and cocoa. Blend well.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread marshmallow cream over cake while still warm.

title: golden chocolate treasure cookies
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Blend Crisco, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, then add chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: vanilla frozen yogurt
directions: Combine sugar, gelatin and salt in a medium saucepan.
Mix in milk and let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
Let cool.
Stir in yogurt and vanilla.
Chill.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to instructions.
Serve immediately or let ripen 1 hour. Yields 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill in refrigerator approximately 30 minutes. Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Drop balls, one at a time, into hot mixture. Remove with fork.
Place on waxed paper.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternately with 1 1/2 cups milk. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: malted milkshakes
directions: Put 4 glass tumblers into the refrigerator to chill for 30 minutes.
Put half the ice and half the ice cream into blender with half the cocoa, sugar, milk and malt.
Blend for 2 minutes until frothy.
Pour into 2 of the chilled tumblers.
Top with scoop of ice cream (if desired).
Use the remaining half ingredients to make the other 2 shakes.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Mix prepared mustard and currant jelly in chafing dish or saucepan over low heat.
You could use a crock-pot on low.
Use either 'Lil Smokies or frankfurters and add to sauce and heat through.
Serve hot.

title: standby bran muffins
directions: Mix the 2 cups bran cereal and boiling water. Let stand. Cream sugar and shortening. Sift together dry ingredients. Add eggs, one at a time, to shortening mix. Beat well after each addition. To this, add buttermilk and remaining 4 cups bran cereal. Stir in bran-water mixture. Add dry ingredients. Fold until moist. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 96 muffins.

title: holly's potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes (leave chunky).
Chop onion and celery. Place in a 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Add water barely to top of potatoes.
Simmer until soft but not mushy.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and 1 tablespoon sugar with pastry blender.
Add just enough ice water to hold dough together. Roll out on floured board to about 1/8-inch thick.
Line the sides and bottom of a 2 to 2 1/2-quart baking dish with crust.
Flute edges of sides.
Cut remaining dough into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces. Set aside.

title: baked stuffed cucumbers
directions: In a large saucepan, cover potatoes with cold, salted water; cover and bring to a boil.
Drain immediately and plunge into cold water.
Drain.
Grate the potatoes into a bowl.
Toss with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until sizzling.
Tilt to coat the surface of the pan.
Add potatoes and press firmly into a large pancake, using the back of a wooden spoon or a spatula.
Cook for about 5 minutes or until bottom is golden brown.
Using a knife or a spatula, loosen the potato cake and slide it onto a large plate.
Drizzle the remaining butter and oil over the uncooked side.
Invert the skillet over the potato cake and carefully turn over so that the potato cake falls into the skillet.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes longer over medium-high heat or until the underside is golden brown.
Loosen and slice onto a serving platter.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix these well and add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of Christian living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile.
Serves:
All.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Stir together the cornstarch into boiling water in a saucepan. Boil for 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Cover and cool.
Beat the egg whites and a dash of salt until foamy.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Beat into cornstarch mixture.
Put on top of baked pie and bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: In a covered pan, cook potatoes until tender; drain well. Peel and cube potatoes.
Put in a large bowl.
Add celery, onion and sweet pickle.

title: will's brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients and bake according to package directions.
Yum!

title: italian salad
directions: Wash and cut all vegetables, amount to your desire.
Add salad dressing and marinate.
Use salad dressings for vegetarian.

title: scalloped turnips
directions: Butter a one-quart casserole.
Layer 1/3 turnips, top with 1/3 onion, sprinkle with 2 teaspoons flour and 1/3 teaspoon salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon butter.
Repeat this layering twice. Combine milk and cream and pour over turnips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for another 30 to 45 minutes or until tender and bubbly.

title: barbecued bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon into pieces to fit chestnuts. Wrap bacon around chestnuts and stick with a toothpick. Continue to do each chestnut this way. Lay in baking dish. Mix ketchup and sugar together and pour over chestnuts. Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook lemon juice, sugar, salt and egg all together over low heat until it thickens.
Cool.
Whip the cream until very stiff. Fold into the sauce mixture and add the fruit.
You may also add 1/2 package miniature marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cracker candy
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with foil.
Spray with a cooking spray such as Pam.
Arrange crackers to cover pan without overlapping. In a saucepan, melt together butter and brown sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes or so.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 4 or 5 minutes (no longer, or it will burn).
Remove from oven; pour chips over the top.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then spread chips evenly over crackers.
Freeze to harden.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in 2 pie shells at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes, until done.
Spread margarine over top of pie and brown.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Drain beans; save 1/3 cup juice.
In saucepan, heat onion and all remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over beans in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: yummir pork chops
directions: Spread each side of pork chop with prepared mustard.
Mix the dry ingredients together.
Roll the mustard pork chops in the dry ingredients.
Put oil in frying pan and brown pork chops on both sides.
Place pork chops in casserole.
Scatter sliced onion on top and pour the soup and water which have been stirred together over the top.
Place in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sausage and stuffing appetizers
directions: Melt butter with water.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Add egg and sausage.
Blend with hands.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls.
Cut bacon slices in thirds.
Wrap around balls and insert toothpicks. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put in bowl.
Mix up.
Put it in pan.
Cook it 1 1/2 hours at 200°.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Crumble 20 Oreo cookies; combine with melted oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: five hour stew(delicious)
directions: Put in large Pyrex baking bowl in order of ingredients given. Bake in a 275° oven for 5 hours.
Tightly cover and don't peek.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place in casserole pan.
Put potato slices on top of pork chops.
Mix 2 cans mushroom soup with 1 can water and pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Prepare meat and vegetables. Dissolve bouillon in water. Combine soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch and sugar, then add to bouillon mixture. In a large heavy skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil over high heat.
Add garlic and meat, then stir-fry for 2 minutes (meat will be slightly pink in the center).
Remove meat juices and set aside.
Wipe pan and heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Add onion, mushrooms, green pepper and water chestnuts. Stir-fry 2 minutes over high heat.
Now, add remaining 1 tablespoon vegetable oil around edge of pan. Add meat juices, then bouillon mixture. Stir, cover and let cook for 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fat-free french fries
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into French fry shape.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam spray.
Place potatoes on pan and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake in a 425° oven about 20 minutes.
Take spatula and turn.
Bake until done and browned.

title: biscuit hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Line the bottom of the pan with 1 tube of biscuits.
Brown the hamburg and onion together, adding salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Drain and pour over biscuit layer.
Pour the spaghetti sauce over the hamburg.
Cover the sauce with 3/4 cup cheese.
Roll out the other tube of biscuits and place it on the top.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on the biscuit layer and cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Drain sauerkraut well.
Cut up cheeses and corned beef into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in dish, cover and bake 10 minutes.
Stir, cover again and cook 10 more minutes.
Serve on bread.

title: cheesy hamburger zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown beef over medium heat.
Drain off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine juice, water, italian seasoning and garlic.
Mix well.
Spray 9 inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Add cooked beef, rice and half the tomato juice mixture.
Mix well.
Top with zucchini, tomato and onion, Pour in remaining tomato juice mixture.
Cover and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes more, or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In a large skillet, fry hash browns; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add onions and green peppers.
Pour in same skillet.
Cook and stir until eggs are set.
Remove from heat. Add hash browns and sausage.
Mix gently.
Place about 3/4 cup of filling on each tortilla and top with about 1/4 cup cheese.
Roll up and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail delight dessert
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda and salt in large bowl.
Mix margarine, cocoa and water together and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 15 x 2-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub and bake the potatoes. Scoop out inside of potatoes and set aside for other use (mashed potatoes, potato salad, etc.). Rub inside of skins with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion salt or garlic salt.
Place potato skins under broiler until skins are crisp.
Mix cubed chicken and cheeses together.
Fill potato skins and return to broiler until cheese is melted.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: italian baked eggplant
directions: Bake eggplant wrapped in foil at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut unwrapped eggplant lengthwise; remove pulp, mash and reserve. Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil in skillet until lightly browned.
Stir in seasonings.
Mix into mashed eggplant.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add to eggplant. Beat egg white with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Add with bread crumbs to eggplant; mix well.
Fill eggplant shells.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marble cake(rhode islander recipe of the week, 1953)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually, and beat until very light.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
To 1/3 of the batter, add the chocolate and blend well.
Drop spoonfuls of batter, alternating light and dark, into a greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Combine Butter Buds and flour in saucepan; add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat.
Beat Egg Beaters, salt, and lemon juice together.
Add some of the first mixture to this before slowly adding to the Butter Buds, flour, and water.
Cook until the spoon is well coated.
This is delicious, easy to make, and will keep well.
It is just as good warmed over as it is fresh off the stove.
Yields 1 1/2 cups (six 1/2-cup servings).

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Check at 45 minutes.)

title: cocktail sauce(no. p-17)
directions: Thin tomato catsup or chili sauce with vinegar.
Add a little sugar to cut vinegar edges.
Use about 2 parts catsup to 1/2 part vinegar.
Season with salt, crushed garlic, red pepper, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish.
Serve with seafood.
Yields 100 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Add onion soup mix to boiling water, then add spaghetti.

Cook until tender; drain well. Cook onion and green pepper in butter until wilted, 5 minutes or so. Add zucchini and cover; cook until tender. Add tomatoes and seasonings. Cook 3 minutes, then turn contents into 2-quart casserole. Add spaghetti and mix well. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Beat one egg into mixture at a time.
Grease four 1-pound coffee cans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Fill each can 1/2 to 3/4 full.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: betty's sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve on bread or buns.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup flour to put on fruit, coconut and nuts. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to mixture.
Combine floured fruit and nuts with batter and pour into large tube pan that has been well-greased (I always line bottom with wax paper).
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: moms soup
directions: Cook potatoes until about done.
Put frozen vegetables and potatoes in soup pot.

title: paint brush cookies
directions: Mix sugar, soft shortening, honey, egg and vanilla in bowl. Mix flour, soda and salt in another bowl.
Mix dry ingredients into shortening mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°. Lightly grease baking sheet.
Divide chilled dough into 3 portions.
Put 2 portions in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: oyster parmesan with caper butter
directions: Thoroughly dry oysters and roll them in grated Parmesan.
Dip them in a mixture of eggs with cream and then in bread crumbs. Put the oysters on absorbent paper on a rack to allow the coating to set.
Melt enough butter in a skillet to cover the bottom to about 1/4-inch and in it, saute the oysters for about 2 minutes on each side, or until they are lightly browned and just beginning to crisp.

title: caramel apples
directions: You will also need 5 wooden sticks.

title: texas hash(weight watchers)
directions: Brown turkey, onions and pepper until tender.
Mix with the remaining ingredients and put into covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: freezer fruit salad
directions: Boil water and sugar; cool.
Combine all other ingredients. Stir in sugar syrup.
Put in containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw until slushy.
(You may want to add fresh strawberries, kiwi or other fruits in season.)

title: shoneys strawberry pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients in pan. Cook until thick, remove from heat and add jello and food coloring. Cool. Place strawberries in baked pie shell, pour filling over strawberries and chill in refrigerator. Garnish with cool whip.

title: spicy taco dip
directions: Combine yogurt and tomato paste and blend well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for a few hours, if possible. Serve with taco chips or vegetables.

title: banana nut bread(this is a doubled recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour alternately with bananas.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix everything together but jello.
Pour dry jello over other mixed ingredients.
Chill.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in order, then set aside. Mix together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture, mixing well, then stir in optional ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove while still warm.

title: green bean bake
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam. Mix together all ingredients; bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Stir-fry rice and green onions.
Add seasoning mix (I bought at Bi-Lo) and 2 teaspoons soy sauce.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Push rice to side.
Add eggs and scramble.
Stir into rice.
Add peas and carrots and meat (optional) and heat.
Makes 5 servings, about 1 cup each as prepared.
Total fat:
0 g, cholesterol 0 mg and 380 mg sodium.

title: cloud sponge cake
directions: Stir together flour,
baking powder and salt; set aside. In large bowl of
mixer,
beat
egg
yolks
at high speed until thick and lemon-colored.	Gradually
beat
in
water until pale and foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until completely dissolved, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Beat in juice and orange rind.
Fold in flour mixture in 3
additions into yolk mixture; set aside.
In small bowl of mixer,
using
clean beaters, beat egg whites and cream of tartar
until
stiff.
Gently
fold into batter.
Pour mixture into a
10-inch
ungreased tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about
hour	or
until
cake springs back when lightly touched.
Invert pan
on neck of bottle and cool.
When completely cooled, use
thin
bladed
knife to loosen cake from pan.

title: mother's chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and put in a Pyrex dish.
Mix broth and soup together.
Heat well and pour over chicken.
Mix flour with buttermilk and spread over chicken. Melt margarine and spoon over top.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven. Serves 6.

title: irene's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with plenty of water for 1 hour; debone.
Roll out dough from biscuits.
Cut or drop into chicken.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes.
Add milk and flour; mix together first.
Simmer for a couple of minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, vanilla and zucchini together.
Mix the remaining ingredients together then add to the liquid mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chips together and spread over the top.
Let cool.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; add condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add lemonade that is slightly thawed.
Pour into graham cracker crust or cooked crust.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite sizes.
Line bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan with tortillas, cut into bite sizes, then spread on chicken. Saute onion and celery in margarine; sprinkle over chicken.
Mix chiles and soup; spread over chicken.
Spread the rest of the tortillas on top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy cabbage-and-beef rolls
directions: Remove 10 outer leaves of cabbage.
Cover leaves with boiling water; cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine 1/2 cup tomato sauce and next 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Place 1/3 cup of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold 2 opposite ends over, and place rolls, seam side down, in a lightly greased 8 inch baking dish.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, sugar, and lemon juice; pour cabbage rolls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cabbage rolls to a serving platter; drain tomato sauce mixture into a saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and water, stirring until smooth; stir into tomato sauce mixture. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Yield:
10 rolls (4 to 5 servings).

title: garden spiral salad
directions: Bring water to a boil in saucepan.
Add spiral noodles and boil approximately 8 minutes.
When cooking time is over rinse noodles with cold water until completely cold.
Drain.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard
boil
eggs.
Peel
eggs
and place in narrow deep jar. Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, cloves and bay leaf in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for
5 minutes.
Pour
hot vinegar solution over eggs, making sure eggs are completely covered with the liquid.
Place onion slices on top of
eggs.
Cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator and let stand several days.
Eggs
may be served whole, halved or sliced;
plain or either
in
sandwiches
or salads.
For a special holiday touch, add a
bit
of
red
food
coloring
to liquid to tint eggs while they are marinating.

title: ice cream bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and corn syrup together.
Add Cocoa Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze until hard. Add ice cream to 1/2 side of pan.
Cut in 1/2 and place on top of ice cream.
Cut into bars.

title: poule anglais
directions: Saute or bake the chicken.
(If sauteed, use 1 cup white wine, I use 1 cup water to saute.)
Cook completely.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together meats, seasonings and eggs.
Add tomatoes and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Bake in a 2-quart loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
This serves 8 to 10.

title: irish cream liquor
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake before using.
Tastes like Bailey's Irish Cream.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine all cans of soup in a crock-pot.
Mix well.
Mix in 1/3 of milk, then add rest.
Cook frozen broccoli in microwave. Add to soup and milk; mix well.
Add pepper for seasoning.
Makes a full crock-pot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Into large bowl, add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add sugars, egg, vanilla and butter.
Beat until smooth and well combined.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet (2-inches apart).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove.
Cool.
Yield:
About 3 dozen.

title: chicken livers with pineapple and almonds
directions: Blanch almonds and set aside.
Mix sugar, brown sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Gradually add, stirring constantly, a mixture of the reserved pineapple syrup, pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Bring rapidly to boiling, stirring constantly. Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Keep hot.

title: herb cheese spread for raw vegetables
directions: Put all ingredients, except chives, in blender or food processor and until smooth.
Cover and chill to blend flavors. Sprinkle with chives. Makes 1 cup.

title: apple dump cake
directions: "Dump" all ingredients together in a large bowl and stir until well mixed.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Dust warm cake with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: parmesan chicken(serves 12)
directions: In a 1-gallon food storage bag, combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and paprika.

Dip chicken in butter. Shake 2 pieces at a time in the bag to coat with crumb mixture. Arrange in 2 (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch) baking pans lined with aluminum foil; sprinkle any remaining coating mixture over the chicken.
(At this point the chicken can be covered tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerated up to 6 hours.)

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix butter, marshmallows, cocoa and Coke together and heat until butter and marshmallows are melted.
Mix well and pour over flour mixture and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Mix soda into buttermilk and then add to mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade make-up
directions: For a smooth and thin make-up cream, blend one part cornstarch and two parts shortening with food coloring.

title: glazed ham balls
directions: In a large bowl combine ham, pork, crushed saltines and eggs. Mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place in two ungreased 15x10x1 baking pans.
Bake uncovered at 350°F for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, vinegar, and mustard in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cook and stir until thickened.
Drain ham balls.
Pour syrup over ham balls.
Bake until glazed or for 10 minutes.
Decorate with freshly cut parsley.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt
butter
in
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or cake pan. In
a
saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until particles are fine.
Add milk and stir
only
until the dough leaves the sides of the bowl. Turn out
onto
lightly
floured surface and knead just until smooth. Roll
dough
into
a
large
rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in other ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes, until lightly brown. Makes 3 dozen.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: saute mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms, peppers and onion.
Add garlic, basil, parsley, paprika, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and A.1. sauce.
Saute about 1 hour in olive oil and butter until done on low heat.
Good on barbecue, steak, hamburgers, etc.
Serves 4.

title: chicken a la crisp
directions: Dip chicken halves in beaten eggs with salt, pepper and parsley.
Then roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Place in 400° oven to heat and melt cheese.

title: cheese-zucchini casserole
directions: Break crackers into casserole dish. Layer the zucchini slices, then tomato slices, then onion slices.
Make another layer of zucchini, tomato and onion.
Sprinkle salt, garlic salt and oregano over top of layers.
Cover with the cheese slices and top with the bacon.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: georgia apple cake
directions: Sift together twice, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. In separate bowl, beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix until a stiff dough forms.
Stir in apples and pecans.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
In large mixing bowl combine chili powder, tomato sauce and half of the grated cheese.
Mix well.
Combine ground beef and tomato mixture.
Add cooked spaghetti and mix.
Place ingredients into 3 quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: arkansas chicken
directions: Rinse Streak 'O Lean in cold water, then put in a mixing bowl. Cover with cold water.
Add honey. Let stand at least 1 hour. Remove one piece at a time and coat with buttermilk.
Roll in flour and fry in a shallow amount of oil until crisp.

title: low-fat carrot muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and butter.
Cut these ingredients like you would for a pie crust. All big chunks of butter should be gone and just have a coarse even mixture.
The better it is blended, the more flaky the scones.

title: pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter and shortening. Add 1 cup sugar at a time and cream.
Add flour and milk and continue creaming.
When completely mixed, add baking powder and cream some more.
Add flavoring and mix well before pouring into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: dijon chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine mustard and water; dip the chicken pieces and then roll in stuffing.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with the remaining stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until juices run clear.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frozen cranberry salad
