directions: Mix with mixer the cranberry sauce and cream cheese. Add all other ingredients, stirring until Cool Whip is smooth. Freeze overnight.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6-inch).
Melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs, stir well. Press on bottom of dish.
In bowl, mix together sweetened milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread pie filling over creamy layer. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly, mix nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over pie filling.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin and put one layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Slice onion and make second layer on top of potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, small chunks of butter and sprinkle with flour. Repeat layers until ingredients are used.
Pour milk in casserole dish until you can see it coming up on the sides of the casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done, about one hour.

title: pumpkin chocolate chips
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Spoon teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Prepare mix ahead; keep in airtight container and use as needed.
When ready to bake cookies, use 3 cups of this mix and add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
I sometimes substitute lemon flavoring or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until barely golden.
Do not overbake.

title: toffee
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar (firmly packed) in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil for 8 minutes.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet that has been sprinkled with chopped nuts.
Place 2 Hershey bars on top; spread, then sprinkle with nuts.

title: freeze ahead crabbies
directions: Melt butter and cheese together.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread on muffins.
Cut muffins into quarter pieces.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Broil until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute tops in butter and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Fill each top with a mound of mix.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Broil for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Crush the graham crackers; set aside.
Melt in a saucepan the peanut butter, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth. Remove from stove.
Stir in the crushed graham crackers; mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: broccoli quich
directions: Beat Bisquick, milk, eggs and oleo until blended together. Fold in cheeses and broccoli. Coat sides and bottom of 9 x 13 pan with a little oleo. Add mixture and bake at 350° about 1/2 hour or until side gets light brown and center is cooked. This is good warm or cold.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 3/4 cup beet juice.
Combine vinegar, reserved beet juice and cornstarch.
Heat beets in double boiler with butter and sugar.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring frequently.

title: skillet pork chops stroganoff style
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook pork chops until well browned on both sides.
Remove pork chops to plate.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; pour off drippings except for 2 to 3 tablespoons.
Add onion and cook until browned.
Add mushrooms and cook.
A dash of garlic may be added here.
Add cooked potatoes.
Mix well and add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for a minute or two.
Crumble bacon over chowder.
Top each serving with a touch of butter.

title: southern refrigerator rolls
directions: To sweet milk, add sugar and shortening.
Put in saucepan and bring to boiling point; let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in the warm water.
Stir in 6 cups flour.
Let rise in a warm place 2 hours.
Then add 5 more cups flour, salt and baking powder, which have been sifted together.
Grease top of dough and cover carefully with waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator until needed.
Allow 1 1/2 to 2 hours for final rising after rolls are in the pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix the first 4
ingredients
and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Drain off all excess liquid.
Mix
and
pour the next 3 ingredients over the
cukes.
Leave
in refrigerator overnight. Then put in jars and refrigerate.
Will keep 6 to 9 months.

title: taco stew
directions: In a skillet brown ground beef.
Drain and rinse with hot water to remove excess fat.
Put ground beef in a Dutch oven and add the rest of ingredients (except tortilla chips and cheese). Simmer on low heat until bubbly and hot.

title: pudding delight
directions: Boil together water and butter, then add flour.
Blend and cool for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Spread on a greased jelly roll pan but don't go to the edges.
It spreads during baking.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Leave cool, then press down.

title: apple peach plum cake
directions: Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Blend in butter.
Break egg in cup and add enough milk to measure 2/3 cup. Mix together.
Pour into pan.
Overlap fruit slices.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked apricots
directions: Grease baking dish.
Layer apricots in dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Drizzle butter over crackers.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: german slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, bell pepper and cover with sugar.
In small sauce pan, combine Wesson oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: sunshine orange mousse pie
directions: In blender, sprinkle gelatin over cold water, let stand 1 minute.
Add hot cream and process at low speed until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese, juice, sugar and vanilla.
Process until well blended.

title: mexican chicken corn chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken, onions and garlic in butter until chicken is not pink.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Oil only bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in the pan.
Make cake mix as directed and put in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of cake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh fruit and dip
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and Fluff together until smooth, then chill. Assemble in divided serving dish the fruit with the dip in center. Put toothpicks in the pineapple and strawberries for serving.

title: lutie flournoy's tamale pie
directions: Mix well and bring to a boil.
Add corn meal to consistency of mush.
Boil slowly for 15 minutes, then bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until tender, but still firm. Immediately rinse in cold water and drain well.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Heat cranberry juice cocktail to boiling.
Stir in raspberry gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Chill until mixture is thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in mold or serving dish.
Chill until firm.
Good with all poultry or pork. Nice on a holiday buffet.
(Recipe may be doubled.)

title: joe's medley of julienne veggies
directions: Wash and clean veggies.
Peel carrot, zucchini and squash. Julienne all veggies (cut lengthwise into 1/4 x 1/4 x 7-inch long strips).
In a large frying pan, cover bottom with olive oil (I only use virgin olive oil).
Heat and when hot, add veggies. Stir-fry for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Cover for a few minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.
They should be crispy and crunchy.
A very colorful meal.
Serves 4.

title: jumer's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set aside.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix Bisquick and cold water; add yeast and let set for 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Pat each part into 4 x 12-inch strip, on a floured board.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with 1/4 sugar/cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat with other pieces.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: candied flowers
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a jar. Shake until color is mixed. Pick only perfect leaves and just open blossoms. Leave enough stem to hold on to. Wash and dry or shake free of dirt. Beat the egg white

just until slightly frothy. Use a small soft camel's hair brush. Be sure to cover all surfaces. If necessary, use a toothpick to separate petals. Sprinkled coated leaf or flower with superfine granulated sugar. Be sure all petals and leaves are sugared top and bottom. Hold over a bowl to save excess for reuse. Put on wax paper on a warm dry place for 2 days. Store in a tightly covered container. Put wax paper between layers.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk together.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch greased pan: tortillas, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 soup mixture, 1/2 onion and 1/2 cheeses.
Will make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix in top of double boiler; stir until thick. Layer in bottom of dish the vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and filling.
Layer again.

title: verna's "wacky or crazy" cake(no milk, no eggs)
directions: Sift together in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Spread evenly.
Make 3 wells in sifted ingredients.
Put oil in one well, vinegar in another well and vanilla in third well.
Pour water over all.
Blend thoroughly with fork, but do not beat.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti squash with summer vegetables
directions: Wash spaghetti squash and cut in half lengthwise; remove and discard seed.
Place squash, cut side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; add 1/4 cup water to dish.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave at High for 20 to 22 minutes, rotating and rearranging at 8-minute intervals.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Drain spaghetti squash and cool.
Remove 4 cups spaghetti-like strands using a fork and set aside.
Reserve any remaining spaghetti squash for use in other recipes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, take out and debone.
Boil spaghetti in chicken water.
Saute as much seasoning as needed in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat until bubbling. Add chicken and spaghetti to heated mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until good and hot (20 minutes).

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can mix it up the day before you serve.
The longer it sets the better it is.

title: chocolate bit cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heart attack on a bun
directions: Slice large loaf of sour French bread into 2 halves.
Soften cream cheese and butter and mix together with garlic until creamy. Spread on open face of bread and cover with grated Cheddar cheese and chopped green onions.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Then broil until cheese bubbles.

title: the colonel's ketchup gravy(it's a guy thing!)
directions: Melt butter in pan, add onions, then bologna.
Stir and add ketchup, spices, and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Blend all ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Shake.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: spinach-mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter in medium skillet until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain spinach thoroughly.
Stir into skillet. Stir in eggs, sour cream, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes until hot.

title: patches(mom's best)
directions: Mix together and roll on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired squares and drop into boiling meat broth (ham, chicken or beef).
Can have meat and cut up potatoes in same large pot.
Also known as slippery pot pie.

title: 1-2-3 fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a full boil (235° on a candy thermometer) for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into large buttered pan.
Cool.
Garnish with more nuts if desired.

title: ham salad party snack
directions: Mix well. Adjust seasonings. Will make 1 1/2 cups of mix. Serve on crackers or as a dip.

title: cornbread batter
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk; blend well.
Pour in hot greased pan.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: carl's crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not pare cucumbers.
Thinly
slice.
Add onions and peppers in a large bowl.
Add salt and cover with ice cubes or cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: pretzel snacks
directions: Mix oil, garlic power, dill and dressing mix together.
Pour over pretzels and mix well.
Let stand at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: sour-salty pickles
directions: Heat all 3 together; do not boil.
Heat until it begins to form bubbles and scum.
Do not pack cucumbers in sterile jars tight.
Pour over cucumbers in jars; do not seal.
Put old lids on jars.
Reheat next day; do not seal.
Reheat the third day; seal. Remember do not boil.
Makes about 11 quarts.

title: chess cheese cake
directions: Mix one egg, butter and cake mix together.
Pat out in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Mix powdered sugar and 2 eggs, vanilla and cream cheese.
Blend together with electric mixer.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown. Cool and cut into bars.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine cream, vinegar, salt, sugar, mustard and pepper.
Mix well.
Add shredded cabbage and toss lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together, add gradually to the egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla and cardamon.
Fold in 1 cup blueberries. Pour half the batter into a well greased and floured pan, 9 x 13 x 2 inch.
Cover with remaining blueberries.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 - 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove to rack to finish cooling.
To serve cut into 12 pieces.

title: summertime beef
directions: Put flank steak in crockpot. Mix remaining ingredients and pour into crockpot over steak. Cook for several hours in crockpot on low. Cut into strips and serve.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender but not overcooked.
Drain and place in bottom of a casserole dish.
Top with sliced cheese, enough to cover the broccoli.
Make enough crumbs to cover the cheese.
Pat with margarine and bake until cheese melts.

title: fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Add nuts and dates.
Beat eggs and vanilla in another bowl and add to first mixture.
Add cherries.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake 90 minutes.

title: potatoes and artichokes, greek style
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the oil lightly.
Add parsley, potatoes and chicken stock.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are barely tender.
Add artichokes; simmer, covered, for another 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna-dill spread
directions: Take pumpernickel, sourdough or any bread and spread with butter.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Fry, dice and drain sausage and then remove from large skillet.
Put milk in bottom of same skillet.
Cut Velveeta into chunks and add to skillet along with salsa.
Stir constantly until cheese melts (scorches easily).
When cheese has melted, add sausage back to the mixture and serve immediately.
It may be kept warm in a crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: challah
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover. Let stand in warm place.
Place butter in mixing bowl with salt and boiling water.
When melted, add oil, sugar and honey.
Add 6 eggs, one at a time.
Mix at low speed.
Add yeast, mix 4 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and knead 10 minutes on table dusted with flour.
Add flour to knead.
Put in buttered bowl and turn, butter side up.
Cover, let rise 1 hour, until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise again 1 hour until doubled.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add butter, mustard, dry onions and poppy seed together.

title: summer slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cabbage, carrots, celery and red onion.
Set aside. Stir together the remaining ingredients and toss with the cabbage mixture.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Bake in pie shell until firm, about 45 to 50 minutes. Garnish with chopped nuts or whipped cream.

title: barbee baked beans
directions: Pour pork and beans in an ungreased casserole dish; add onion, brown sugar, molasses, salt, pepper, mustard, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Blend together; place the bacon strips on top of beans and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until desired consistency. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: southwestern grilling marinade
directions: Note - This marinade is great for beef, poultry, pork, and lamb.
1. Combine all ingredients in a non-metal bowl. Marinate
meat for at least 30 minutes.
2. Grill meat to perfection and enjoy.

title: angela's favorite white cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together Crisco and almond extract.
Gradually add 1 1/3 cups sugar to shortening and extract.
Cream well.
Add milk alternating with dry ingredients (start and end with flour).
Beat the 5 egg whites and 1/3 cup sugar until peaks form.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes for sheet cake.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Before cooking, sprinkle top with
crushed
Ritz
crackers.
Bake
minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fillets in foil
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix margarine and lemon juice and dill weed; reserve.
Place each frozen fillet in center of individual piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil (spray with Pam).
Drizzle each fillet with a scant tablespoon margarine mixture.
Top with 2 slices onion.
Arrange potato and carrot on sides and fill top with beans.
Seal foil tightly.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until fillets flake easily with fork and vegetables are tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil the fresh squash in salted water until tender; drain. If using frozen squash, cook according to package and drain. Combine squash with butter, soup, sour cream, onion, carrot and 1 cup stuffing.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-walnut drop cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Add flour and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing.
While warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: frosted apricot jewels
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter and cream cheese until coarse. Add coconut and preserves, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Spread each cookie with frosting. Top with pecan half.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place length of foil on flat surface.
In large bowl, beat shortening, brown sugar, water and vanilla on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, beating on low speed just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheet to foil.
Cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cherry coffee cake internationale
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray two 9-inch round cake pans. Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Add extract.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide batter into pans; spread fruit on top.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: flavored vodka
directions: *Buffalo grass can be purchased in health food stores.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Sweeten sliced strawberries to taste; set aside.
Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water.
Whip cream until foamy.
Add dissolved gelatin slowly, continuing to whip.
Add vanilla; whip until stiff.
Drain juice from strawberries; fold berries into whipped cream.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill. Garnish with whole strawberries, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine soup, cream cheese, lemon juice, green onion, curry powder, garlic powder and hot sauce in mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed until of serving consistency.
Chill, covered, for several hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli and grapes.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to broccoli grape mixture.
Toss and chill.
Before serving, add bacon and nuts.
Toss.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower(very good)
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Add water. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 or 9 minutes or until tender and crisp.
Combine salad dressing, onion and mustard in bowl.
Spoon over top of cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave on roast for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes to heat topping and melt cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Soak cracked wheat in water for 30 minutes.
Dice parsley, scallions and tomatoes.
Squeeze out cracked wheat and mix with spices, lemon juice and oil.
Add diced vegetables and mix thoroughly.
(Diced vegetables are parsley, scallions and tomatoes.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, drain off fat.
Add all ingredients.
Cook slowly until well mixed.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Thaw frozen bread.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut each loaf in half and then in half again lengthwise.
Then cut in pieces the size of a walnut and put 1 loaf in pan.
Mix all the rest of ingredients together real well.
Put on top of first loaf in pan. Put second cut-up loaf on top of mixture.
Let rise.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Cool about 15 minutes and invert on tray or plate.
Nuts may be added if desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Form into flat ovals and fry in hot fat.

title: dave's own fried rice
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and set aside.
Scramble eggs; set aside.
Prepare rice; let cool.
Put rice in skillet with a little butter.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add ground beef, eggs, peas and cook for about 10 minutes or until thoroughly warm.
Press into small bowl or mold.
Put on plate upside down.
Go back and take off bowls and serve piping hot.
Accent can be used as seasoning.

title: hawaiian special macnut cookies
directions: Cream the butter or margarine, white sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture. Stir in gently the chocolate chips, Hershey bar, macnuts and Rice Krispies.
Drop with tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Makes about 55 (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients very well (3 to 4 minutes).
Pour in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. While cake is still hot, poke holes in it with fork.
Pour glaze made of 2 cups powdered sugar and 6 to 10 tablespoons of lemon juice over cake.
Refrigerate.
Serve with no frosting.

title: cherry brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into a long cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and cream.
Add pecans.
Drop onto a buttered foil and chill.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; bring to a full boil.
Let boil for 1 minute; remove from heat, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop onto paper to cool by the tablespoonfuls.

title: quick tuna squares
directions: In large bowl, with fork combine all ingredients until mixed and smooth.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dunking platter cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in oatmeal and cornflakes.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Chill and serve with chips.

title: "cold water iced tea"
directions: Fill a one quart jar with cold water.
Add tea bags and cover. Chill in refrigerator 12 to 18 hours or overnight.
Remove tea bags and pour into tall glasses filled with ice.
Offer juicy lemon wedges and sugar to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in a separate bowl. Mix oil and eggs and add to dry ingredients. Stir until moistened, then stir in pecans last. Pour in sheet pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares when cool.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter, 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla, water and flour.
Mix well; add nuts.
Form rolls 1 1/2 inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.
While hot, roll in rest of powdered sugar.
Place on wax paper and cool.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine cinnamon and alum.
Gradually add applesauce until the mixture becomes crumbly, not sticky.
Knead vigorously for about 5 minutes.
Mixture should be pliable.
Roll out to 1/4-inch and cut with cookie cutters of desired shapes.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet and allow to dry for 3 days, turning 5 times a day.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Shape mixture into small meatballs. Mix remaining ingredients for sauce.
Heat.
Drop meatballs into sauce, cover, and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
about 48 meatballs.

title: fudge sheet cake
directions: Place in large bowl the sugar and flour.
Set aside.
Bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured 11 x 16-inch (like jelly roll pan) at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread frosting on cake when removed from oven while hot.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Cream shortening, butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Then add first mixture.
Add oats and coconut.
Roll dough in walnut-size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Top with walnut or pecan halves. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix boiling water and sugar with Jell-O.
Cool and add pineapple.
Chill this and add Dream Whip.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Tear angel food cake into tiny bits and put in pan.
Pour the mixture over cake.
Put Cool Whip over this and top with coconut.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: Combine beans, bourbon, brown sugar, coffee powder, mustard and lemon juice.
Turn into individual bean pots or casseroles. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pina colada
directions: Blend in blender on blend.

title: potato candy(or poor man's candy)
directions: Boil potato.
Remove skin.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar until you make a dough (depends on amount of water in potato).
Roll out with rolling pin (use sugar to dust surface).
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into jelly roll (about 1 1/2-inch roll).
Slice in 1/4-inch bars.

title: ernestine's drop biscuits
directions: Have iron skillet sizzling hot.
Drop by tablespoon into hot skillet. Bake at 450° about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 small biscuits.

title: yellow squash hush puppies
directions: Chop the onion and add to squash.
Beat egg and fold in.
Add salt, flour and meal.
Mix well.
Mixture should be medium-soft. Drop by teaspoon into hot cooking oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: tuna and noodle au gratin
directions: Make a white sauce of margarine, flour, milk and seasonings. Add cheese and stir until smooth on low heat.

title: broiled fish
directions: Mix butter, juice, salt and pepper.
Baste fillets with sauce and place in broiler pan.
Broil about 5 minutes on each side, basting with sauce when fillets are turned.
Place on warm plate and pour remaining sauce over fish.
Serve immediately.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: In large frypan, simmer oil, garlic, onion, parsley and red pepper until onion is transparent and garlic lightly browned.
Add diced tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Meanwhile, cook pasta al dente (12 to 15 minutes).
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Put pasta in serving bowl; pour sauce over pasta.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: skillet cornbread or corn pone
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together in a bowl.
Add the shortening.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together with your hands until the mixture is crumbly.
Pour in the buttermilk, a little at a time, and stir with a wooden spoon until a dough is formed.
Shape into a ball and return to the bowl.
Set aside.

title: 10-minute peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix the sugar, syrup and salt. Microwave at High for 5 minutes. Stir in peanuts. Microwave at High for 2 to 6 minutes or until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned, stirring after every 2 minutes of cooking time. Stir in the butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy. Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on a large, well-buttered cookie sheet.
Makes 1 pound peanut brittle.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Boil quartered potatoes in salted water until soft.
Mash hot potatoes; add milk.
Fold in cheese and egg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese) to meat; bring to boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Do not drain any ingredient, except meat grease.
Serves 12.

title: mother's fried chicken
directions: It is important that the chicken is coated with flour and refrigerated overnight.
Use a covered Tupperware mixing bowl or rectangular pan.

title: party ham ball
directions: Reserve 4 slices ham.
Mix all ingredients together by hand. Shape into ball and chill overnight.
Before serving wrap 4 pieces of ham around ball and secure with toothpicks.
Serve with crackers.
(Chop ham before combining with other ingredients.)

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add spaghetti sauce and heat. Boil egg noodles and drain.
Add hamburger mix to egg noodles. Cut strips of cheese and put in with the hamburger-egg noodle mix. Heat until cheese is melted, constantly stirring to keep from sticking.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Pour melted margarine into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour batter over margarine to cover bottom of pan.
Place peaches on top of batter.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375° and continue baking until golden brown.
Serves 16.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Set aside. Combine sugar and oil.
Beat until well blended.
Beginning and ending with dry ingredients, add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce to sugar mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: my favorite fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, strawberries and oranges.
Mix with the peach pie filling and add sliced bananas.
I sometimes add miniature marshmallows or coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: the lady's cheese mac
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
After macaroni has been boiled and drained, add cheddar cheese while macaroni is still hot.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to macaroni mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with additional cheese, if desired.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Beat together egg yolks, melted butter and milk.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk mixture to dry mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Pour into unbaked crusts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until done (about 1 hour).

title: dietetic hawaiian pork chops
directions: In large skillet sprayed with Pam, cook onion and green pepper until onion is clear; remove from skillet.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chops, one at a time.
Shake to coat meat.
Brown chops in skillet.
Place pineapple slice on top of each chop.
Sprinkle with onion and green pepper.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Dough will be soft.
Turn onto floured board and knead a few times, adding flour to make dough firm enough to roll out.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut out with cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Yields about 36 (2-inch) rolls.

title: tomatillo salsa
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend. Refrigerate. Superb with chips and on Mexican food.

title: easy veg-all potato casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Cook according to directions on box.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: ham balls
directions: Make into balls.
Put in covered baking dish with the sauce.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, mayonnaise, and chili powder.
Layer half of each:
meat mixture, chips, and cheese in 2 qt casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shell salad
directions: Boil sugar and water for 1 minute.
Cool; blend into Miracle Whip.
Cook shells until tender.
Rinse well with cold water.
Put shells, peas, onion and tuna in bowl.
Toss lightly.
Pour dressing over and mix well.
Serve in 3 hours or can let set overnight.
(This gives dressing time to absorb into pasta.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir together broccoli, rice, onion and celery, soup and Cheez Whiz. Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownie torte
directions: Bake one package brownie mix according to directions in two round cake tins.
Cool.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash the bean mixture well, then cover with water.
Add salt. Soak at least 3 hours or overnight.
Put beans (after draining) in 2 quarts water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook all day or at least 4 hours.
Remove ham bone and excess fat.

title: special mint bars
directions: Crush 1/2 of Oreos and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Whip the cream.
Fold in mints and marshmallows and spread on top of Oreo crumbs.
Crush remaining Oreos and spread on top of whipping cream mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.
